{"type":"message","id":"4e8ee71d","parentId":"51b9bed7","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:48:13.903Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"function.exec:4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 /home/node/.openclaw/skills/tavily-search/scripts/search.py --query \"Apple Vision Pro 工业设计 最新案例 2024 2025\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":4491,"output":51,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4542,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772941691788}}
{"type":"message","id":"c2ba14a1","parentId":"4e8ee71d","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:48:14.880Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"function.exec:4","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"--query\",\n  \"response_time\": 1.46,\n  \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n  \"answer\": \"The `--query` parameter in AWS CLI filters JSON output using JMESPath syntax. It processes the entire response before displaying, which can be slower for large datasets. It replaces the need for external tools like `jq`.\",\n  \"images\": [],\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/v1/userguide/cli-usage-filter.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Filtering output in the AWS CLI - AWS Command Line Interface\",\n      \"content\": \"## Client-side filtering\\n\\nThe AWS CLI provides built-in JSON-based client-side filtering capabilities with the `--query` parameter. The `--query` parameter is a powerful tool you can use to customize the content and style of your output. The `--query` parameter takes the HTTP response that comes back from the server and filters the results before displaying them. Since the entire HTTP response is sent to the client before filtering, client-side filtering can be slower than server-side filtering for large data-sets.\\n\\nQuerying uses JMESPath syntax to create expressions for filtering your output. To learn JMESPath syntax, see Tutorial on the JMESPath website.\\n\\n###### Important\\n\\nThe output type you specify changes how the `--query` option operates: [...] The following example lists Amazon EC2 volumes using both server-side and client-side filtering. The service filters a list of all attached volumes in the `us-west-2a` Availability Zone. The `--query` parameter further limits the output to only those volumes with a `Size` value that is larger than 50, and shows only the specified fields with user-defined names.\\n\\n```\\n{{\\n```\\n\\nThe following example retrieves a list of images that meet several criteria. It then uses the `--query` parameter to sort the output by `CreationDate`, selecting only the most recent. Finally, it displays the `ImageId` of that one image. [...] To extract information from a specific item\\n\\nThe following example uses the `--query` parameter to find a specific item in a list and then extracts information from that item. The example lists all of the `AvailabilityZones` associated with the specified service endpoint. It extracts the item from the `ServiceDetails` list that has the specified `ServiceName`, then outputs the `AvailabilityZones` field from that selected item.\\n\\n```\\n$ aws --region us-east-1 ec2 describe-vpc-endpoint-services \\\\ --query 'ServiceDetails[?ServiceName==`com.amazonaws.us-east-1.ecs`].AvailabilityZones' [ [ \\\"us-east-1a\\\", \\\"us-east-1b\\\", \\\"us-east-1c\\\", \\\"us-east-1d\\\", \\\"us-east-1e\\\", \\\"us-east-1f\\\" ] ]\\n```\\n\\nTo show snapshots after the specified creation date\",\n      \"score\": 0.8003337,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@fayas_akram/use-query-parameter-for-aws-cli-output-instead-of-jq-6fa25c55ea0a\",\n      \"title\": \"Use Query parameter for AWS CLI Output instead of jq - Medium\",\n      \"content\": \"Sitemap\\n\\nOpen in app\\n\\nSign in\\n\\nSearch\\n\\nSign in\\n\\n# Use Query parameter for AWS CLI Output instead of jq\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\n3 min read\\n\\n·\\n\\nJul 3, 2022\\n\\n--\\n\\nThe AWS CLI provides built-in JSON-based client-side filtering capabilities with the `--query` parameter. The `--query` a parameter is a powerful tool we can use to customize the content and style of our output. The — query parameter takes the response from the server and filters the results before displaying them. This is very useful, especially for storing the output to variables.\\n\\n> Note: Since the entire response is sent to the client before filtering, client-side filtering can be slower than server-side filtering for large data sets.\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n### AWS CLI Query filtering Examples [...] `{“container name”: name, “port”: portMappings[].containerPort}` is used to label the Name and portMapping(nested array) as a port and container name respectively. Later, `[?port==``].”container name\\\"` Label port is used to query the container name with port 80.\\n\\n### Conclusion\\n\\nThe AWS CLI provides client-side filtering capabilities with the `--query` parameter. It is a powerful tool when it comes to filtering, transforming, and customizing content as we needed. It completely eliminates the use of jq Linux command.\\n\\n### Reference\\n\\nAWS CLI Docs: \\n\\nAws Cli\\n\\nJq\\n\\nLinux\\n\\nAWS\\n\\nAws Ecs\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\n## Written by Fayas Akram\\n\\n242 followers\\n\\n·629 following\\n\\n## Responses (1)\\n\\nText to speech [...] ### AWS CLI Query filtering Examples\\n\\n1. Query Output\\n2. Identifiers (Keys)\\n3. Filter by identifiers\\n4. Filter value by expression\\n5. Set labels to output values\\n\\n### Query Output\\n\\nThe output type changes define how the --query option should operate.\\n\\nWhen we specify `--output text`, the output is paginated before the --query filter is applied. This might result in unexpected extra output due to the query runs once on each page of the output. To additionally filter the output, you can use other command-line tools such as `head or tail` .\\n\\nWhen we specify `--output json`, `--output yaml`, or `--output yaml-stream` the output is completely processed as a single, native structure before the `--query` filter is applied.\\n\\n### Identifiers\",\n      \"score\": 0.73778254,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.azurecitadel.com/cli/jmespath/\",\n      \"title\": \"JMESPATH queries - Azure Citadel\",\n      \"content\": \"Azure Citadel\\n\\nJMESPATH queries;)\\n\\nJMESPATH queries\\n\\n# JMESPATH queries\\n\\nUnderstand the JMESPATH queries using this lab that explores some common uses.\\n\\n## Table of Contents\\n\\n## Introduction\\n\\nThe `--query` switch is one of the “global” switches, i.e. it is available on every az command, and it enables you to query and filter the output of the command.\\n\\nThe Azure CLI uses the industry standard JMESPATH query format that is used not only by the CLI, but also the AWS CLI and other commands that need to manipulate JSON.\\n\\nThere is some excellent documentation on JMESPATH at the official site, and it covers the full range of what can be accomplished. This guide will give you a shortcut into the commonly used functionality when querying Azure JSON output.\\n\\n## JSON Format [...] Each of the commands below follow `az resource list --resource-group myAppRG-Staging --query '' --output json` format. Only the query switch will be shown in the table below for the sake of brevity.\\n\\n| Query | Output |\\n --- |\\n| `--query '[]'` | Pass through the whole array |\\n| `--query '[]'` | Flatten the array |\\n| `--query ''` | First entity |\\n| `--query '[-1]'` | Last entity |\\n| `--query '[a:b]'` | Array slice from a to b-1 |\\n\\nIf you omit either the a or b value from a slice then the slice array goes to the start or end, e.g. `'[:2]'` gives the first two elements (i.e. 0 and 1), whereas `'[2:]'` will give all remaining elements from a list, from element 2 onwards. [...] ## Selecting Object Values\\n\\nYou can also be selective on the name:value objects.\\n\\nQuerying on the name for a name:value pair is trivial and simply state the name. Use the `az account show --query '' --output json` command to show your active Azure subscription.\\n\\n| Query | Output |\\n --- |\\n| `--query 'name'` | Cosmetic name for the subscription |\\n| `--query 'id'` | The ID for the subscription |\\n| `--query 'user'` | The user object for the subscription |\\n| `--query 'user.name'` | The value for name within the user object |\\n\\nThe last example above shows a nested value, pulling the value of name in the user object.\\n\\nWhen pulling out individual values, the tsv output format will omit the braces and quotes, making it simple to read into a variable. For example:\",\n      \"score\": 0.71113056,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46160592/aws-cli-filtering-output-with-query-and-filter\",\n      \"title\": \"aws-cli - Filtering output with --query and --filter - Stack Overflow\",\n      \"content\": \"### Post as a guest\\n\\nRequired, but never shown\\n\\n### Post as a guest\\n\\nRequired, but never shown\\n\\nBy clicking “Post Your Answer”, you agree to our terms of service and acknowledge you have read our privacy policy.\\n\\nStart asking to get answers\\n\\nFind the answer to your question by asking.\\n\\nExplore related questions\\n\\nSee similar questions with these tags.\\n\\n#### Linked\\n\\n#### Related\\n\\n#### Hot Network Questions\\n\\n# Subscribe to RSS\\n\\nTo subscribe to this RSS feed, copy and paste this URL into your RSS reader.\\n\\n##### Stack Overflow\\n\\n##### Business\\n\\n##### Company\\n\\n##### Stack Exchange Network\\n\\nSite design / logo © 2026 Stack Exchange Inc; \\nuser contributions licensed under \\nCC BY-SA\\n. \\nrev 2026.3.4.40455 [...] ### current community\\n\\n### your communities\\n\\n### more stack exchange communities\\n\\nCommunities for your favorite technologies. Explore all Collectives\\n\\nStack Overflow for Teams is now called Stack Internal. Bring the best of human thought and AI automation together at your work.\\n\\nBring the best of human thought and AI automation together at your work.\\nLearn more\\n\\n##### Collectives™ on Stack Overflow\\n\\nFind centralized, trusted content and collaborate around the technologies you use most.\\n\\nStack Internal\\n\\nKnowledge at work\\n\\nBring the best of human thought and AI automation together at your work.\\n\\n# aws-cli - Filtering output with --query and --filter\\n\\nConsider I want to query aws cli for an instance list that have the tag:\\n\\nrole=myrole [...] ## 1 Answer 1\\n\\nThe only piece missing in your command is to ensure that the tag `myId` is present and has a non-empty value. That filter has to be applied to the selected instances (`Instances[]`). How to filter for that is covered in another answer on Stack Overflow and integrating it into your command is rather straight forward:\\n\\n`myId`\\n`Instances[]`\\n`aws ec2 describe-instances \\\\\\n--filter \\\"Name=tag:role,Values=myrole\\\" \\\\\\n--query \\\"Reservations[].Instances[?Tags[?Key=='myId' && Value!='']].[InstanceId,Tags[?Key=='myId'].Value]\\\"`\\nDunedan's user avatar\\n\\n## Comments\\n\\nAdd a comment\\n\\n## Your Answer\\n\\nThanks for contributing an answer to Stack Overflow!\\n\\nBut avoid …\\n\\nTo learn more, see our tips on writing great answers.\\n\\n### Sign up or log in\\n\\n### Post as a guest\\n\\nRequired, but never shown\",\n      \"score\": 0.4613328,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.vocabulary.com/dictionary/query\",\n      \"title\": \"Query - Definition, Meaning & Synonyms - Vocabulary.com\",\n      \"content\": \"SKIP TO CONTENT\\n\\n/ˈkwiri/\\n\\nIPA guide\\n\\nOther forms: queried; queries; querying\\n\\nA query is a question, or the search for a piece of information.\\n\\nThe Latin root quaere means \\\"to ask\\\" and it's the basis of the words inquiry, question, quest, request, and query. Query often fits the bill when referring to Internet searches, polite professional discourse, and subtle pleas. You could query as to the whereabouts of the lavatory, but you'd sound a bit prim and be better off asking \\\"Where's the toilet?\\\" If your job entails dealing with annoying questions and complaints, you could make it sound better by proclaiming, \\\"I respond to customer queries.\\\"\\n\\nDefinitions of query\\n\\n1. an instance of questioning\\n\\n   synonyms:  enquiry, inquiry, interrogation, question\\n\\n   see moresee less\\n\\n   type of:\",\n      \"score\": 0.41151342,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"request_id\": \"91f00667-81bd-4df1-ac16-bba9f4935383\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":979,"aggregated":"{\n  \"query\": \"--query\",\n  \"response_time\": 1.46,\n  \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n  \"answer\": \"The `--query` parameter in AWS CLI filters JSON output using JMESPath syntax. It processes the entire response before displaying, which can be slower for large datasets. It replaces the need for external tools like `jq`.\",\n  \"images\": [],\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/v1/userguide/cli-usage-filter.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Filtering output in the AWS CLI - AWS Command Line Interface\",\n      \"content\": \"## Client-side filtering\\n\\nThe AWS CLI provides built-in JSON-based client-side filtering capabilities with the `--query` parameter. The `--query` parameter is a powerful tool you can use to customize the content and style of your output. The `--query` parameter takes the HTTP response that comes back from the server and filters the results before displaying them. Since the entire HTTP response is sent to the client before filtering, client-side filtering can be slower than server-side filtering for large data-sets.\\n\\nQuerying uses JMESPath syntax to create expressions for filtering your output. To learn JMESPath syntax, see Tutorial on the JMESPath website.\\n\\n###### Important\\n\\nThe output type you specify changes how the `--query` option operates: [...] The following example lists Amazon EC2 volumes using both server-side and client-side filtering. The service filters a list of all attached volumes in the `us-west-2a` Availability Zone. The `--query` parameter further limits the output to only those volumes with a `Size` value that is larger than 50, and shows only the specified fields with user-defined names.\\n\\n```\\n{{\\n```\\n\\nThe following example retrieves a list of images that meet several criteria. It then uses the `--query` parameter to sort the output by `CreationDate`, selecting only the most recent. Finally, it displays the `ImageId` of that one image. [...] To extract information from a specific item\\n\\nThe following example uses the `--query` parameter to find a specific item in a list and then extracts information from that item. The example lists all of the `AvailabilityZones` associated with the specified service endpoint. It extracts the item from the `ServiceDetails` list that has the specified `ServiceName`, then outputs the `AvailabilityZones` field from that selected item.\\n\\n```\\n$ aws --region us-east-1 ec2 describe-vpc-endpoint-services \\\\ --query 'ServiceDetails[?ServiceName==`com.amazonaws.us-east-1.ecs`].AvailabilityZones' [ [ \\\"us-east-1a\\\", \\\"us-east-1b\\\", \\\"us-east-1c\\\", \\\"us-east-1d\\\", \\\"us-east-1e\\\", \\\"us-east-1f\\\" ] ]\\n```\\n\\nTo show snapshots after the specified creation date\",\n      \"score\": 0.8003337,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@fayas_akram/use-query-parameter-for-aws-cli-output-instead-of-jq-6fa25c55ea0a\",\n      \"title\": \"Use Query parameter for AWS CLI Output instead of jq - Medium\",\n      \"content\": \"Sitemap\\n\\nOpen in app\\n\\nSign in\\n\\nSearch\\n\\nSign in\\n\\n# Use Query parameter for AWS CLI Output instead of jq\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\n3 min read\\n\\n·\\n\\nJul 3, 2022\\n\\n--\\n\\nThe AWS CLI provides built-in JSON-based client-side filtering capabilities with the `--query` parameter. The `--query` a parameter is a powerful tool we can use to customize the content and style of our output. The — query parameter takes the response from the server and filters the results before displaying them. This is very useful, especially for storing the output to variables.\\n\\n> Note: Since the entire response is sent to the client before filtering, client-side filtering can be slower than server-side filtering for large data sets.\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n### AWS CLI Query filtering Examples [...] `{“container name”: name, “port”: portMappings[].containerPort}` is used to label the Name and portMapping(nested array) as a port and container name respectively. Later, `[?port==``].”container name\\\"` Label port is used to query the container name with port 80.\\n\\n### Conclusion\\n\\nThe AWS CLI provides client-side filtering capabilities with the `--query` parameter. It is a powerful tool when it comes to filtering, transforming, and customizing content as we needed. It completely eliminates the use of jq Linux command.\\n\\n### Reference\\n\\nAWS CLI Docs: \\n\\nAws Cli\\n\\nJq\\n\\nLinux\\n\\nAWS\\n\\nAws Ecs\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\nFayas Akram\\n\\n## Written by Fayas Akram\\n\\n242 followers\\n\\n·629 following\\n\\n## Responses (1)\\n\\nText to speech [...] ### AWS CLI Query filtering Examples\\n\\n1. Query Output\\n2. Identifiers (Keys)\\n3. Filter by identifiers\\n4. Filter value by expression\\n5. Set labels to output values\\n\\n### Query Output\\n\\nThe output type changes define how the --query option should operate.\\n\\nWhen we specify `--output text`, the output is paginated before the --query filter is applied. This might result in unexpected extra output due to the query runs once on each page of the output. To additionally filter the output, you can use other command-line tools such as `head or tail` .\\n\\nWhen we specify `--output json`, `--output yaml`, or `--output yaml-stream` the output is completely processed as a single, native structure before the `--query` filter is applied.\\n\\n### Identifiers\",\n      \"score\": 0.73778254,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.azurecitadel.com/cli/jmespath/\",\n      \"title\": \"JMESPATH queries - Azure Citadel\",\n      \"content\": \"Azure Citadel\\n\\nJMESPATH queries;)\\n\\nJMESPATH queries\\n\\n# JMESPATH queries\\n\\nUnderstand the JMESPATH queries using this lab that explores some common uses.\\n\\n## Table of Contents\\n\\n## Introduction\\n\\nThe `--query` switch is one of the “global” switches, i.e. it is available on every az command, and it enables you to query and filter the output of the command.\\n\\nThe Azure CLI uses the industry standard JMESPATH query format that is used not only by the CLI, but also the AWS CLI and other commands that need to manipulate JSON.\\n\\nThere is some excellent documentation on JMESPATH at the official site, and it covers the full range of what can be accomplished. This guide will give you a shortcut into the commonly used functionality when querying Azure JSON output.\\n\\n## JSON Format [...] Each of the commands below follow `az resource list --resource-group myAppRG-Staging --query '' --output json` format. Only the query switch will be shown in the table below for the sake of brevity.\\n\\n| Query | Output |\\n --- |\\n| `--query '[]'` | Pass through the whole array |\\n| `--query '[]'` | Flatten the array |\\n| `--query ''` | First entity |\\n| `--query '[-1]'` | Last entity |\\n| `--query '[a:b]'` | Array slice from a to b-1 |\\n\\nIf you omit either the a or b value from a slice then the slice array goes to the start or end, e.g. `'[:2]'` gives the first two elements (i.e. 0 and 1), whereas `'[2:]'` will give all remaining elements from a list, from element 2 onwards. [...] ## Selecting Object Values\\n\\nYou can also be selective on the name:value objects.\\n\\nQuerying on the name for a name:value pair is trivial and simply state the name. Use the `az account show --query '' --output json` command to show your active Azure subscription.\\n\\n| Query | Output |\\n --- |\\n| `--query 'name'` | Cosmetic name for the subscription |\\n| `--query 'id'` | The ID for the subscription |\\n| `--query 'user'` | The user object for the subscription |\\n| `--query 'user.name'` | The value for name within the user object |\\n\\nThe last example above shows a nested value, pulling the value of name in the user object.\\n\\nWhen pulling out individual values, the tsv output format will omit the braces and quotes, making it simple to read into a variable. For example:\",\n      \"score\": 0.71113056,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46160592/aws-cli-filtering-output-with-query-and-filter\",\n      \"title\": \"aws-cli - Filtering output with --query and --filter - Stack Overflow\",\n      \"content\": \"### Post as a guest\\n\\nRequired, but never shown\\n\\n### Post as a guest\\n\\nRequired, but never shown\\n\\nBy clicking “Post Your Answer”, you agree to our terms of service and acknowledge you have read our privacy policy.\\n\\nStart asking to get answers\\n\\nFind the answer to your question by asking.\\n\\nExplore related questions\\n\\nSee similar questions with these tags.\\n\\n#### Linked\\n\\n#### Related\\n\\n#### Hot Network Questions\\n\\n# Subscribe to RSS\\n\\nTo subscribe to this RSS feed, copy and paste this URL into your RSS reader.\\n\\n##### Stack Overflow\\n\\n##### Business\\n\\n##### Company\\n\\n##### Stack Exchange Network\\n\\nSite design / logo © 2026 Stack Exchange Inc; \\nuser contributions licensed under \\nCC BY-SA\\n. \\nrev 2026.3.4.40455 [...] ### current community\\n\\n### your communities\\n\\n### more stack exchange communities\\n\\nCommunities for your favorite technologies. Explore all Collectives\\n\\nStack Overflow for Teams is now called Stack Internal. Bring the best of human thought and AI automation together at your work.\\n\\nBring the best of human thought and AI automation together at your work.\\nLearn more\\n\\n##### Collectives™ on Stack Overflow\\n\\nFind centralized, trusted content and collaborate around the technologies you use most.\\n\\nStack Internal\\n\\nKnowledge at work\\n\\nBring the best of human thought and AI automation together at your work.\\n\\n# aws-cli - Filtering output with --query and --filter\\n\\nConsider I want to query aws cli for an instance list that have the tag:\\n\\nrole=myrole [...] ## 1 Answer 1\\n\\nThe only piece missing in your command is to ensure that the tag `myId` is present and has a non-empty value. That filter has to be applied to the selected instances (`Instances[]`). How to filter for that is covered in another answer on Stack Overflow and integrating it into your command is rather straight forward:\\n\\n`myId`\\n`Instances[]`\\n`aws ec2 describe-instances \\\\\\n--filter \\\"Name=tag:role,Values=myrole\\\" \\\\\\n--query \\\"Reservations[].Instances[?Tags[?Key=='myId' && Value!='']].[InstanceId,Tags[?Key=='myId'].Value]\\\"`\\nDunedan's user avatar\\n\\n## Comments\\n\\nAdd a comment\\n\\n## Your Answer\\n\\nThanks for contributing an answer to Stack Overflow!\\n\\nBut avoid …\\n\\nTo learn more, see our tips on writing great answers.\\n\\n### Sign up or log in\\n\\n### Post as a guest\\n\\nRequired, but never shown\",\n      \"score\": 0.4613328,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.vocabulary.com/dictionary/query\",\n      \"title\": \"Query - Definition, Meaning & Synonyms - Vocabulary.com\",\n      \"content\": \"SKIP TO CONTENT\\n\\n/ˈkwiri/\\n\\nIPA guide\\n\\nOther forms: queried; queries; querying\\n\\nA query is a question, or the search for a piece of information.\\n\\nThe Latin root quaere means \\\"to ask\\\" and it's the basis of the words inquiry, question, quest, request, and query. Query often fits the bill when referring to Internet searches, polite professional discourse, and subtle pleas. You could query as to the whereabouts of the lavatory, but you'd sound a bit prim and be better off asking \\\"Where's the toilet?\\\" If your job entails dealing with annoying questions and complaints, you could make it sound better by proclaiming, \\\"I respond to customer queries.\\\"\\n\\nDefinitions of query\\n\\n1. an instance of questioning\\n\\n   synonyms:  enquiry, inquiry, interrogation, question\\n\\n   see moresee less\\n\\n   type of:\",\n      \"score\": 0.41151342,\n      \"raw_content\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"request_id\": \"91f00667-81bd-4df1-ac16-bba9f4935383\"\n}","cwd":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/researcher"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772941694877}}
{"type":"message","id":"677ab4b3","parentId":"c2ba14a1","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:48:23.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"搜索脚本似乎有问题，让我直接使用 tavily 搜索技能来调研 Apple Vision Pro 的工业设计案例："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"function.exec:5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/node/.openclaw/skills/tavily-search && python3 -c \"\nfrom tavily import TavilyClient\nimport json\n\nclient = TavilyClient()\n\n# 搜索 Apple Vision Pro 工业设计相关案例\nqueries = [\n    'Apple Vision Pro industrial design case study 2024 2025',\n    'Apple Vision Pro 工业设计 案例',\n    'Apple Vision Pro spatial design industrial applications',\n    'Apple Vision Pro manufacturing automotive design',\n    'Vision Pro CAD 3D modeling industrial use'\n]\n\nresults = []\nfor q in queries:\n    try:\n        res = client.search(query=q, max_results=5, search_depth='advanced')\n        results.append({'query': q, 'results': res.get('results', [])})\n    except Exception as e:\n        results.append({'query': q, 'error': str(e)})\n\nprint(json.dumps(results, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\n\"","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":6723,"output":257,"cacheRead":640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772941694884}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5440a7e","parentId":"677ab4b3","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:48:38.456Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"function.exec:5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro industrial design case study 2024 2025\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.scribd.com/document/864576806/Apple-Vision-Pro-Development-A-Case-Study\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro Development A Case Study | PDF - Scribd\",\n        \"content\": \"The Apple Vision Pro, introduced in 2024, represents a watershed momentin spatial computing that transcends conventional boundaries o augmentedand virtual reality. This case study presents a comprehensive analysis o the device’s journey rom conceptualization through commercialization, ex-amining the intricate interplay o research breakthroughs, design iterations,and strategic decisions that shaped its development. Through investiga-tion o patent portolios, technical documentation, and industry analyses, wetrace how Apple’s decade-long investment in undamental technologies—rommicro-OLED displays and eye-tracking systems to the custom-designed M2and R1 silicon architecture—culminated in this ambitious product. Thestudy delves deep into critical phases o product development, [...] Apple, Apple Vision Pro, Augmented Reality (AR), VirtualReality (VR), Product Design, Innovation\\n\\nPreprint submitted to Elsevier January 4, 2025\\n\\nDownload to read ad-free\\n\\nApple Vision Pro: A Privacy Overview\\n\\nFrom Scribd3 pages70 views\\n\\nApple Vision Pro: A Privacy Overview\\n\\nNo ratings yet\\n\\n1. Introduction [...] 15 pages\\n Exploring VR and AR Technologies\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Exploring VR and AR Technologies\\n\\n  3 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro Product Overview\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Apple Vision Pro Product Overview\\n\\n  2 pages\\n Apple Product Innovations 2024-2025\\n\\n  \\n\\n  100% (1)\\n\\n  Apple Product Innovations 2024-2025\\n\\n  282 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro: Future of AR Technology\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Apple Vision Pro: Future of AR Technology\\n\\n  13 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro Report\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Apple Vision Pro Report\\n\\n  16 pages\\n Future Computing Trends and Innovations\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Future Computing Trends and Innovations\\n\\n  3 pages\\n Advancements in HCI Technologies\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Advancements in HCI Technologies\\n\\n  10 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro Marketing Insights\",\n        \"score\": 0.82895297,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@jlacuna1031/case-history-of-apples-vision-pro-development-process-implementation-9448b715e0d0\",\n        \"title\": \"Case History of Apple's Vision Pro Development Process ... - Medium\",\n        \"content\": \"Sitemap\\n\\nOpen in app\\n\\nSign in\\n\\nSign in\\n\\n# Case History of Apple’s Vision Pro Development Process & Implementation\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\n4 min readNov 6, 2025\\n\\nDeveloping a new product and bringing it to market is neither particularly fast nor easy; most companies have a process for doing so, often a variation of the New Product Development (NPD) process. A great example in the real world is Apple and its recent release of the headset Vision Pro. To an outsider, it may seem that Apple simply decided to create this product one day, but in reality, a lengthy process brought it from a thought to customers’ hands.\\n\\n## Idea Generation [...] ## Get Jose Acuna’s stories in your inbox\\n\\nJoin Medium for free to get updates from this writer.\\n\\nReferences\\n\\n-Apple Inc. (2024, June 5). Introducing Apple Vision Pro: Apple’s first spatial computer. Apple Newsroom. \\n\\n-Robertson, A. (2023, June 5). Apple Vision Pro is Apple’s new $3,499 AR headset. The Verge. \\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\n## Written by Jose Acuna\\n\\n0 followers\\n\\n·1 following\\n\\n## No responses yet\\n\\nWrite a response\\n\\nWhat are your thoughts?\\n\\n## More from Jose Acuna\\n\\nHow Starbucks Uses Marketing to Connect With People Everywhere\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\n## How Starbucks Uses Marketing to Connect With People Everywhere\\n\\n### Before this marketing class, I did not think about how much strategy goes into something as simple as buying coffee. After reading Chapters…\\n\\nOct 24, 2025\",\n        \"score\": 0.79522943,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.aalpha.net/articles/apple-vision-pro-use-cases-and-applications/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro Use Cases and Applications 2025 - Aalpha\",\n        \"content\": \"Furthermore, the product is more versatile and gives users an incredible feeling of innovation and realism. With these great innovative features, Apple Vision Pro serves well in refining prototypes, sketching designs, and 3D modeling.\\n\\n ## Education\\n\\nEducation is another crucial sector that has grown thanks to Apple Vision Pro. Users have seen a more engaging and innovative education process with the product. With the tool, it is more accessible to actualize distance learning. Surprisingly, users can have multiple distance learning sessions all at once. The tool has more significant support for e-learning and teleconferencing, among others. [...] ## Entertainment and social space\\n\\nThe entertainment and social space is more welcoming and appealing, thanks to Apple Vision Pro. It comes with high-quality displays, support for spatial audio, and anything entertaining any user would love to experience. With Vision Pro, expect to immerse yourself in a theater-like experience in the living spaces. Its features allow synchronized viewing for a better and more compelling experience. [...] ## Innovativeness and productiveness\\n\\nApple Vision Pro has a three-dimensional, flexible, innovative, and productive interface. With such an interface, users can easily access the productive right anywhere. The innovative device allows you to maneuver between a range of supported screens easily. Surprisingly, all these happen simultaneously, giving the users an even better experience. With such a better experience, users can easily organize their virtual space even through voice inputs. With the seamless and intuitive experience, users enjoy a productive environment free from disruption, thus enabling faster and easier completion of tasks. The multitasking support makes the experience much better.\",\n        \"score\": 0.7795405,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.idc.com/resource-center/blog/apple-vision-pro-2025-with-m5-a-sharper-vision-for-spatial-computing/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro (2025) with M5: A Sharper Vision for Spatial ... - IDC\",\n        \"content\": \"Siri also continues to lag. In a world where AI assistants are becoming more conversational and context-aware, Apple’s voice interface feels dated. With competitors integrating advanced AI into their headsets, Apple needs to accelerate its efforts here to stay competitive.\\n\\n## Final Thoughts\\n\\nThe 2025 Vision Pro is less of a radical reinvention and more thoughtful refinement. Apple didn’t need to push the tech forward, but it did. And in doing so, it’s made the device more comfortable, more powerful, and more developer-friendly.\\n\\nFor businesses and developers, these changes matter. The M5 chip unlocks new possibilities, the Dual Knit Band improves day-to-day usability, and the continued focus on performance ensures the Vision Pro remains a leader in spatial computing. [...] ## A Subtle but Significant Upgrade\\n\\nAt first glance, the 2025 Vision Pro doesn’t scream “new.” The design remains familiar, and the core experience is still rooted in spatial computing. But the changes Apple has made are thoughtful and impactful.\\n\\nThe most immediately noticeable improvement is the new Dual Knit Band. Comfort has long been a sticking point for head-mounted devices, and Apple’s solution here is elegant. The new band distributes weight more evenly, reduces pressure points, and makes long sessions far more tolerable. It’s a small change that dramatically improves usability for users who wear the headset for hours at a time.\\n\\n## M5: Power, Efficiency, and AI Muscle [...] Skip to main Skip to search Skip to footer\\n\\nBecome a Client\\n\\nBecome a Client\\n\\nTechnologies   October 23, 2025  5 min\\n\\n# Apple Vision Pro (2025) with M5: A Sharper Vision for Spatial Computing\\n\\nShare on LinkedIn   Share on X%20with%20M5:%20A%20Sharper%20Vision%20for%20Spatial%20Computing)\\n\\nApple’s Vision Pro was already a technological marvel when it launched. With its ultra-high-resolution displays, spatial audio, and seamless integration into Apple’s ecosystem, it set a new benchmark for mixed reality. But in 2025, Apple chose not to rest on its laurels. The updated Vision Pro, now powered by the M5 chip, refines the experience in meaningful ways especially for the professionals and developers who rely on it most.\\n\\n## A Subtle but Significant Upgrade\",\n        \"score\": 0.76279575,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://augmentedenterprisesummit.com/looking-back-at-the-most-notable-xr-use-cases-of-2024/\",\n        \"title\": \"Looking Back at the Most Notable XR Use Cases of 2024\",\n        \"content\": \"Though Apple’s headset failed to meet industrial enterprise needs, healthcare and medical professionals proved to be big fans. In breakthrough experiments, Apple Vision Pro assisted in spinal and heart surgeries at London’s Cromwell Hospital and Stanford Health Care in the Bay Area (March) as well as in dozens of surgeries at India’s GEM Hospital in Chennai (May). In all cases, Vision Pro provided consolidated, hands-free access to real-time information about the patient and procedure. \\n\\nMeanwhile, Sharp Healthcare in San Diego established a Spatial Computing Center of Excellence and purchased 30 Apple Vision Pro headsets for workers doing “all sorts of jobs,” and Boston Children’s Hospital created a medical personnel training app for the Vision Pro. [...] Related: Apple Vision Pro: Already a Hit in Healthcare and Retail\\n\\nThe medical industry displayed interest in XR in general, as well: Boston’s Mass General Brigham tested XR for code cart training of new nurses, while surgeons from several departments established the UC Davis Medical Extended Reality (MXR) Research Group.\\n\\n2024 also saw rising interest and even concrete use cases from the public sector, including federal agencies and local governments. Most recently, the U.S. Department of Labor’s Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) expanded its use of Vuzix M400 smart glasses with the aim of reducing response times, improving operational efficiency, and boosting workplace safety. [...] Share\\n\\nShare\\n\\n2024 Enterprise Use Case Trends:\\n\\n –Greater interest in XR from healthcare and the public sector\\n –Training still the top XR application in enterprise (increasingly in combo with AI)\\n –Digital twins are expanding to more and more industries\\n –More reporting of quantifiable ROI\\n –Sustainability as a frequently cited driving factor and benefit of XR\\n –Up-and-coming use cases: PR and employee wellness\\n\\n## Retail, Healthcare, and Government\\n\\nLet’s start with Apple Vision Pro. Vision Pro arrived in February of this year, and numerous brands created apps for the spatial computer. These included popular retailers like Wayfair (Decorify interior design app), J. Crew (Virtual Closet), Lowe’s (Style Studio), and Best Buy (Envision to plan your home technology setup).\",\n        \"score\": 0.7279179,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro 工业设计 案例\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://pdf.dfcfw.com/pdf/H3_AP202312281615148585_1.pdf\",\n        \"title\": \"[PDF] 苹果Vision Pro 硬件顶级配置，内容生态不断搭建\",\n        \"content\": \"Room 采用 Unity 引擎制作， VisionOS 通过与 RealityKit 的深度集成来支持该引擎。 图29：Rec Room 被Vision Pro 列入“我们喜爱的应用程序和游戏” 资料来源：UploadVR，信达证券研发中心 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  18 图30： Rec Room 在Vision Pro 上进行测试 资料来源：UploadVR，信达证券研发中心 Vision Pro 应用行业——工业领域 随着工业数字化转型、工业4.0、智能制造等概念的推广，越来越多的企业开始寻求智能化的工业技术升级， 希望以技术赋能产业，为企业创造新的价值。具体应用环节例如：产品设计、生产制造、巡检维修等。工业产 品设计时可以将想法以全息影像形式立体呈现，缩短开发周期多维度感知设计效果。生产制造环节，MR 技术 可以让用户即刻看到数字影像与真实环境融合的效果，利用MR 技术可即刻查看到工作场景中各个相关线路、 管道及其详细的测量值，并能够高精准度地进行安装、搭建。在工业生产环境中，工作人员也可以戴上MR 眼 镜进行巡检及时准确的发现生产故障。 图31：MR 在工业领域中的应用 资料来源：东孚科技，信达证券研发中心 Vision Pro 应用行业——医疗行业 MR 应用在医疗领域，具体在外科医学教育、医学临床、远程协作及手术导航等细分赛道，有望为新一轮智慧 手术的技术迭代带来新的创新驱动因子。锦瑟医疗通过MR 技术，可以将平面的影像学检查图像重建成3D 数 字模型，投射到手术室的空间中，与真实场景中的患者情况相融合，进而辅助医生实现术前手术规划、手术路 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  19 径模拟、术中辅助定位等，以提高手术的精准性、安全性和成功率。早在2019 年，锦瑟医疗就取得国内第一 张基于混合现实技术的产品注册证。 图32： MR [...] ➢ Pancake 光学方案：Pancake 方案可以折叠光路，从而实现轻薄。Quest 3 使用了2P 的Pancake 方案 并且树立了较高的专利壁垒，苹果采用了3P Pancake 设计，这种方案的优势体现在性能，劣势则在于工 艺和成本。 ➢ 虹膜识别：人的虹膜是唯一的，在出生之后不久便会定型，成长的过程中很难发生改变。苹果搭载了虹 膜识别方案，称为Optic ID。我们也非常看好这一项技术，可以预见，在国内腾讯和海外苹果推动之下， 虹膜识别技术有望快速在VRAR 设备乃至手机等终端迅速普及。 ➢ IPD 调节：Vision Pro 能够自动检测用户的瞳距，并调节两个显示屏的距离，让用户获得最佳视觉体验。 为了满足近视人群需求，苹果还与蔡司合作定制了光学镜片。 ➢ 空间音频：位于耳朵两侧的双驱动单元音频组件能带来沉浸式的空间音频体验。Vision Pro 还能分析空间 的特征和材质，使声音精确匹配物理时空。 此外，苹果还有许多不同程度的创新，例如一整块以 3D 方式成型与压层的玻璃，表面进行光学抛光，用作一 系列摄像头和传感器的镜片，将数字内容与真实世界完美融合。轻质眼罩使用柔软的织物，提供各种尺寸和 形状以适合每一位用户的脸型。可调节松紧的边带确保音频保持靠近用户的耳朵，采用 3D 织法的多种尺寸的 头带不仅舒适、透气且具有弹性。头带透过单一机制固定，容易更换尺寸及造型。 图8：苹果Vision Pro Pancake 光学方案 图9：虹膜识别 资料来源：VR 陀螺，信达证券研发中心 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 图10：Vision Pro 空间音频 图11：Vision Pro 绑带 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  9 [...] EyeSight 反向透视 售价 3499 美元 发售时间 2024 年年初 资料来源：VR 陀螺，信达证券研发中心 硬件端阵容豪华，传感器搭建数字世界感知现实的桥梁。苹果展现出与竞争对手完全不同的路线，在显示、眼 动追踪、手势交互等方面，为了追求良好的效果，苹果Vision Pro 硬件阵容强大，以传感器为例，Vision Pro 搭 载了12 个摄像头、5 个传感器（1 个Lidar、2 个结构光深度传感、2 个IR 传感）和6 个麦克风。 Vision Pro 正面有 2 个主摄像头、4 个向下的摄像头、2 个侧面摄像头。1 个激光雷达分布在中央，两侧各有一 个原深感摄像头，还有两个IR 照明器。在Vision Pro 内侧，有四个红外摄像头和两个LED 补光，主要用于眼 动追踪。 以红外摄像头为例，苹果左右各配备了2 颗红外摄像头，在保障追踪精度的同时，还能测算双眼瞳深，进而实 现更好的画面显示效果，而对手大多只配备一颗。这项技术并不是一项新技术，而出现这种结果，是因为苹果 的Vision Pro 在设计的时候一直以用户作为根本出发点，没有陷入卷成本的“高级游戏机”漩涡。 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  6 图6：Vision Pro 传感器分布 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 苹果Vision Pro 主显示屏采用Micro OLED，单眼分辨率达到4K，这是目前市场上首次出现的使用Micro OLED 实现双目8K 效果的产品。Micro OLED 显示屏具有自发光、能耗低和体积小等特性，可实现更高色域、 分辨率及发光效率等优势，天然适配于近眼显示设备。Micro OLED 采用单晶硅晶圆为背板，接近半导体工艺， 而为了获得更大FOV，需要更大的屏幕支撑，而在屏幕尺寸变大的过程中，除了制造工艺、成本等直线大幅上\",\n        \"score\": 0.80442166,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com.cn/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro 商务应用- Apple (中国大陆)\",\n        \"content\": \"### 借助数字孪生，获取精准指导。\\n\\n在实物旁边，放置一个精细的模型进行对照，还可使用数码分步操作指南，来进一步提升工作效率。有了 BILT 3D Immersive Instructions app，建筑和水电等领域的专业技师能更快、更准确、也更安全地完成工作。\\n\\n一只手将接有电线的机械盒安装在墙上，旁边有 3D 成像的同款设备。\\n一只手将接有电线的机械盒安装在墙上，旁边有 3D 成像的同款设备。\\n\\n## 顾客体验\\n\\n### 吸引顾客， 从心动到行动。\\n\\n劳氏公司 (Lowe’s) 风格工作室\\n\\n### 产品演示看得真实，感受真切。\\n\\n提供沉浸式的产品演示，让顾客以耳目一新的方式配置、试用和购买产品。在保时捷，顾客可使用 Apple Vision Pro，以真实尺寸个性定制梦想座驾，还能以生动愉悦的方式尽情体验。\\n\\n保时捷展厅内，一位佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的顾客一边观看 3D 成像的跑车，一边与工作人员交谈。\\n保时捷展厅内，一位佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的顾客一边观看 3D 成像的跑车，一边与工作人员交谈。\\n\\n### 吸引顾客了解更多，体验更好。\\n\\n以增强现实效果呈现室内设计、提供虚拟产品试用，以及在真实环境中加入视觉特效，众多引人入胜的新方式，带来精彩纷呈的客户体验。借助 JigSpace app，Evapco 等制造业龙头能全面革新客户教育的模式。\\n\\n一间工业厂房中，一个 3D 投影的 EVAPCO 冷却塔，旁边有关于冷却塔的信息可翻阅。\\n一间工业厂房中，一个 3D 投影的 EVAPCO 冷却塔，旁边有关于冷却塔的信息可翻阅。\\n\\n### 无需搭建，产品精彩呈现。\\n\\n顾客能以虚拟的方式欣赏、研究，甚至深入探索产品的内部设计。通过迪卡侬的自定 app，顾客无需打开包装盒，就能体验真实比例的户外装备。 [...] # 放眼新境， 远见企业未来。\\n\\nSpatial Analogue shown in video\\n\\nCAE shown in video\\n\\nVisage Ease VP shown in video\\n\\nPorsche Car Configurator shown in video\\n\\nApple Vision Pro 开启商务应用的无限可能，解锁全然一新的工作方式。团队可在别开生面的工作空间中相互协作、优化工作流程、提升培训效率，并创造一流的客户体验。从制造业、医疗行业，到更广阔的领域，借助 Apple Vision Pro 的空间计算能力，各行各业都能突破革新。\\n\\n## 设计\\n\\n### 设计流程， 彻底重新设计。\\n\\n3DLive\\n\\n### 加快评估进度。\\n\\n无需制作实体样品，就能与世界各地的团队共同审核原型设计，从而加快工作流程。通过 Spatial Analogue 这类 app，相关的各方均可参与其中，还可使用各种空间配件在虚拟物体上标注与绘图。\\n\\n一位头戴 Apple Vision Pro 的设计师，通过手的移动对一把 3D 成像的椅子进行测量。\\n一位头戴 Apple Vision Pro 的设计师，通过手的移动对一把 3D 成像的椅子进行测量。\\n\\n### 细节全面看通透。\\n\\n全球团队都能通过分层 3D 模型，从各个角度查看内部零件。有了 Innoactive 这样的平台，大众汽车等企业能借助视觉化的数码模型，来评估汽车零部件，从而简化设计流程。\\n\\n一只手做出捏合的手势，与 3D 成像的汽车动力传动系统进行互动。\\n一只手做出捏合的手势，与 3D 成像的汽车动力传动系统进行互动。\\n\\n### 空间设计，重塑零售空间。 [...] ### 快速上手，顺畅上岗。\\n\\n通过各种培训单元，帮助员工减少失误，提升学习速度，尽快准备就绪。在荷兰皇家航空公司，技术人员会使用 Engine Shop app，将操作指南叠加在真实比例的大型设备模型上，随后按步骤进行操作。\\n\\n一间工业厂房中，有一个 3D 成像的喷气发动机，另有一个浮窗，显示一系列操作步骤。\\n一间工业厂房中，有一个 3D 成像的喷气发动机，另有一个浮窗，显示一系列操作步骤。\\n\\n### 更低成本，更快精通机械。\\n\\n员工在修理、操作和维护实体设备时，能将所需信息叠加进空间，从而快速掌握大量资讯。ThingLink 可将教程与组件详情直接叠加在机械设备上，一切都一目了然。\\n\\n仓库中的一台大型机械，旁边有一个 3D 成像的窗口，写着“Key Features of the Sabi EB 250”的字样。\\n仓库中的一台大型机械，旁边有一个 3D 成像的窗口，写着“Key Features of the Sabi EB 250”的字样。\\n\\n## 工作指导\\n\\n### 专业指导， 专攻复杂项目。\\n\\nVisage Ease VP\\n\\n### 上手操作设备，说明书不用在手上。\\n\\n员工无需手持说明书，也能浏览数码参考资料，双手都能专注在工作上，令准确度与速度双双提升。在荷兰皇家航空公司，技术人员使用 Engine Shop app 来确定扭矩序列，确保安装顺利无误。\\n\\n飞机库中，一名佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的技术人员使用手中的工具，调整飞机的挡风玻璃。\\n飞机库中，一名佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的技术人员使用手中的工具，调整飞机的挡风玻璃。\\n\\n### 借助数字孪生，获取精准指导。\",\n        \"score\": 0.78944516,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.easemob.com/news/10391\",\n        \"title\": \"Vision Pro 的8 年历程：只有苹果才能这样造产品- 环信\",\n        \"content\": \"堪比 SpaceX 造火箭的投入，只为了解决一些特别基础的需求：\\n\\n 让设备更轻。目前较轻的头戴设备一般 400~500 克。苹果一度提出过 150g 重的头戴设备方案，目标是让人连续佩戴 8 小时。但苹果并没有透露 Vision Pro 的重量，只是强调用了更轻的材料，比如用透气的织物做头带、外接电池。\\n 让画面更真实。苹果搭配了十多个高清摄像头、激光雷达等传感器获取周围的环境，自研两款芯片处理这些图像；定制 4K 分辨率、每秒刷新 120 次的 micro OLED 屏幕显示图像，再经过优化的三层镜片折射，让图像更逼真、通透，最终传递到人眼的视网膜上。VR 行业常用每 1° 视野中像素点（角分辨率，PPD）综合评判头戴设备的显示效果，达到人眼的效果需要到 60。现在的设备普遍只有 20 左右，而 Vision Pro 做到了 40。\\n\\n 让操作更简单。现在的头戴设备几乎都要用控制器操控，苹果认为这是 “恼人的工具”，收购多家面部追踪公司，用多个传感器实时追踪人眼和手势——视线就是鼠标、两指一掐就是点击。\\n 让近视眼有更好的体验。现在近视用户使用头戴设备，要么戴着眼镜把脑袋挤进去，要么贴上近视镜片。苹果是为数不多在发布会上介绍近视用户怎么用设备的公司，它与蔡司合作定制了适合 Vision Pro 的近视镜片，吸附到设备上，可以保证完美的体验。\\n\\n一位参与 Vision Pro 研发的前苹果制造工程师告诉《晚点 LatePost》，对于工业设计师确定的参数，负责制造团队基本没有任何发言权，必须想尽一切办法去实现。\\n\\n具体到近视镜片的硬件模组上，苹果会与供应商一起制定切割镜片的方案，尽可能提前想到用户可能会遇到的极端情况，比如确保磁吸模块能适应不同度数（厚度）的镜片，每个细节都会经过数百上千次的调试，扩大视力矫正范围的同时，不影响显示屏性能或视线追踪的准确性。 [...] 库克常戴不足 30 克重的 MYKITA 眼镜。今天的技术不足以造出这样轻便、高画质的 AR 设备。罗克韦尔的解决办法是，以 VR（虚拟现实）的方式实现 AR（增强现实）：\\n\\n戴上 Vision Pro，用户眼前依然是两块屏幕，看不到外面。但 12 个摄像头、激光雷达和红外传感器捕捉外部画面，实时渲染出实景一般的图像呈现在屏幕上，让人有看穿屏幕的错觉。旋转 Vision Pro 右上方的旋钮，就能从以假乱真的外部世界（AR）切换到沉浸的虚拟空间（VR），比如坐在丛林里看恐怖片。\\n\\n与此同时，苹果还在设备外部加了一块的弧形屏幕，用来显示传感器收集到的用户眼部画面，做出透视的效果。苹果将其称为 EyeSight。\\n\\nVision Pro 内外布满摄像头等传感器。上方是 Vision Pro 外部情况，有 8 个高清摄像头、2 个景深相机、1 个激光雷达。下方是 Vision Pro 内部情况，有 4 个红外摄像头和一圈 LED。图片来自苹果。\\n\\nVision Pro 会在外置屏幕上模拟用户眼部画面。图片来自苹果。\\n\\n为了在 VR 设备上做出一款 AR 眼镜，苹果连续收购了十几家有相关人才和技术的创业公司，自行开发了新处理器、光学镜片模组、操作系统、应用开发平台等关键组件。到研发后期，苹果每年都在这个项目上投入 10 亿美元。\\n\\n堪比 SpaceX 造火箭的投入，只为了解决一些特别基础的需求： [...] 散热较差是苹果将高算力芯片塞进头显中带来的直接问题。直到 2022 年，罗克韦尔与苹果董事会成员展示成品时，散热问题也没有解决，不得不延期发布产品。在发布会上，苹果展现出来的最终解决方案是加上两个风扇帮助散热。\\n\\n前述苹果 Vision Pro 团队前员工告诉《晚点 LatePost》，他感受最深的是苹果对设备细节的关注。2021 年底，一个硬件模组到了量产前最后一个步骤，需要评估最终的质量。\\n\\n苹果测试它从一米、两米、五米的高度掉下来后情况怎样。最后发现，设备从五米处掉落后，包裹镜片的塑料框有万分之一、二的概率会裂开。\\n\\n“从副总裁到基层，整条线上的所有人都介入了，重新设计方案，供应商也重新调整。” 他说。临近产品发布，苹果和供应商的工程师们加班、熬夜去解决这个问题。\\n\\n一个没有工厂的企业，一年花 100 亿美元买设备推动制造技术\\n\\n乔布斯时期，苹果可以很低成本找到关键技术并突破。2003 年，苹果一个 6 人交互设计团队做了一个概念设备，两根手指在屏幕上点点画画，就能拉动网页、放大图片。这就是后来的多点触控，今天每个人在手机上的操控界面。\\n\\n当时苹果刚走出 2000 年纳斯达克崩盘的谷底，工程师们多年不换电脑，多点触控技术在 Windows PC 上完成。但乔布斯组织起 200 多人团队，逼着他们把触控的电脑先做到 iPad 的尺寸，再做到了 3.5 英寸屏幕上，成为 iPhone，彻底改变了我们世界的运作方式，为一代互联网公司搭起创业基础设施。\\n\\n微软研究院的工程师差不多在同期给董事长比尔·盖茨（Bill Gates）演示了多点触控技术。最后在 iPhone 发售前一个月，微软发布了一台桌子大小的触控电脑——Surface Desk。\\n\\n微软 2007 年发布的 Surface，运行一个定制版的 Windows Vista 操作系统。\",\n        \"score\": 0.7606688,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.ednchina.com/news/a13012.html\",\n        \"title\": \"拆解Vision Pro（一）：发现一个非常奇怪的设计\",\n        \"content\": \"Q5eednc\\n\\n当您第一次戴上Vision Pro 时，它本身会自动进行瞳距调整，并通过电机调整镜片的位置。Q5eednc\\n\\n苹果商店有一台机器，可以在您参加演示时确定近似处方眼镜的强度。对于患有可能会干扰眼球追踪的眼部疾病（如斜视）的用户，Vision Pro在辅助功能中提供了替代交互控制。然而，我们听说有散光的人（占人口的 40%）不适合佩戴镜片。Q5eednc\\n\\n处方镜片本身需要与耳机“配对”。这一决定已经带来了糟糕的用户界面，约翰·格鲁伯（John Gruber）在他的审查单元中收到了错误的校准代码，导致眼动追踪表现不佳。原则上我们讨厌零件配对，并且必须有一种方法可以在允许使用第三方镜头的同时进行校准。Q5eednc\\n\\n### R1和M2芯片\\n\\n该耳机在 M2 Mac 芯片上运行，与新的 R1 芯片配合使用，后者专门负责处理来自 12 个摄像头、LiDAR 传感器和 TrueDepth 摄像头的输入，所有这些都具有最小的延迟。使用 AR，您需要尽快将现实世界的摄像头视图投射到用户的眼睛中，否则他们感知到的动作将与他们所看到的不匹配，这就是一张通往 Vomitsville 的快速门票。 Q5eednc\\n\\n为了跟上，R1使用实时操作系统。这意味着任务总是在固定的时间内执行。我们的大多数计算机都运行在分时操作系统上，该操作系统会动态安排任务，并可能导致速度变慢。想想紧张的鼠标光标或旋转的沙滩球，您就明白了。这对于像直通视频和对象渲染这样重要的东西来说是行不通的。那里的任何故障都会像黑客帝国中的故障一样，往好里说会令人不舒服，往坏里说则完全令人作呕。它甚至可能导致您绊倒和跌倒。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n### 一个非常奇怪的设计 [...] Q5eednc\\n\\n### 一个非常奇怪的设计\\n\\n最初的 iPhone 也做了类似的事情。当其动力不足的芯片无法跟上渲染快速滚动的页面时，它会切换到灰白棋盘格，以跟上您所有的轻弹和滑动操作。苹果将响应能力置于图形保真度之上。这一次，他们优先考虑了图形保真度和响应能力，并在电池寿命、重量和热量方面受到了影响。考虑到这种体验对苹果 AR 体验的重要性，这可能是第一代设备的正确选择。Q5eednc\\n\\nVision Pro很重，玻璃很脆弱，而且系绳电池可能会很烦人。但苹果已经成功地将 Mac 的强大功能以及新型专用 AR 芯片的性能整合到一台可以戴在脸上的电脑中。Q5eednc\\n\\n苹果公司在 EyeSight 屏幕上显然花了很多年的时间才创造出来，但它分辨率低，并且给耳机中对重量最敏感的部分增加了大量的体积、重量、复杂性和费用。Q5eednc\\n\\n我们的分析还没有完成：这个设备内部还有很多东西需要研究。下一次，我们将深入研究内部显示器、传感器阵列，并给予可修复性评分。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n 报名IIC Shanghai 2026（3.31-4.1 上海浦东丽思卡尔顿酒店），掌握全球芯动向，领取丰厚福利>>  \\n  \\n2026国际集成电路展览会暨研讨会，聚焦AI 芯片、汽车电子、工业控制、通信系统、绿色能源等关键应用场景，汇聚全球IC 设计、EDA 工具、IP 授权、先进封装等领域的顶尖企业与专家，通过「2 大主题峰会+ 权威奖项评选+ 垂直技术论坛+ 展览展示」四大核心板块，打造贯通芯片设计制造、能源技术革新、产品商业化落地的超级产业连接器。\\n\\n责编：Demi\\n\\n阅读全文，请先 登录 [...] 前置护目镜是 Vision Pro 的标志性特征，现在评论纷至沓来，这也是最具争议性的特征之一。Q5eednc\\n\\nEyeSight 的专利描述了三种显示模式：“内部聚焦”、“外部参与”和“请勿打扰”。该专利有一页又一页的图像可以显示在屏幕上——各种卡通动物的眼睛、其他传感器捕获的生物特征分析、用户与亲人交谈时的心形。内部摄像头可以读取情绪状态并根据这些情绪状态投射图像。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n很酷的想法。实际上，EyeSight 显示屏非常昏暗且分辨率低，评论家表示很难在上面看到太多内容。《华尔街日报》的乔安娜·斯特恩 (Joanna Stern)称其“很难看见”，而马克斯·布朗利 (又名 MKBHD) 则表示，“当我戴着耳机时，你几乎看不到我的眼睛。” Q5eednc\\n\\n事实证明，当 EyeSight 显示你的眼睛时，它不仅仅是显示你眼睛的单个视频；它还显示你的眼睛。它正在显示一堆你眼睛的视频。通过探索玻璃外壳内部，我们发现了前置显示屏的三层：加宽层、透镜层和 OLED 显示屏本身。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n### 为什么视觉看起来如此不稳定？\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\nApple 希望实现一些非常具体的目标：带有眼睛的动画 3D 面孔。为了实现这一目标，他们必须做出非常战略性的设计选择和妥协。Q5eednc\\n\\n人类的大脑对面孔和表情非常敏感，这就是恐怖谷之所以存在的原因，其中一部分就是深度感知。Apple 需要创造可信的 3D 效果。3D 渲染看起来不像真正的 3D 的原因之一是它们缺乏立体效果。为了让某些东西看起来像 3D，我们需要用每只眼睛看到略有不同的图像。Vision Pro 通过双凸透镜解决了这个问题。Q5eednc\",\n        \"score\": 0.6682966,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.realwear.com.cn/news/2306apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro重新定义“远程办公” 给工业端带来无限畅想\",\n        \"content\": \"所以，面对一线作业人员，或者一线使用者来说，衡量一款软件的好坏要从三个维度出发进行判别：\\n\\n\\\"第一，要有非常好的使用体验，毕竟这是一款高度体验的产品。甚至，对于这种软件的体验要求比手机要高的多。一个设备戴在头上，如何跟它进行交互——什么时候用手势，什么时候用眼神，什么时候用语音，这种要求远远高于对手机的要求。针对这一点来讲，不光在硬件上有好的体验，在内容的设计上也要结合硬件提供与之匹配的优秀体验。内容层面，是通过语音交互，还是姿态交互，亦或者根据使用场景自动切换，这些因素都至关重要。所以，关乎软件应用是否足够优秀，它的体验感非常重要。第二，在工业领域或者企业应用领域，要求的不是发散，不是创造性，是收敛，是精准。我们给一线人员提供的，或者给企业管理者提供的数据和应用的结论必须是非常准确的，我们必须要直击一线使用者的痛点，解决他的问题，搜集到正确数据，做出正确的AI判断……所以，它是一个收敛的过程，不是一个发散的过程。这是判断软件应用好的第二个标准，它一定是精准的，不是开放式的，发散式的。第三，我们认为一个好的软件应用，或者工业企业的数字内容，它是一个系统。我们所提供的解决方案所为企业提供的价值，不是单单针对戴设备的人，或者使用者。它是整个工业互联网，或者工业元宇宙世界中的一个终端。除此之外，还有其他的终端、其他的角色。这个角色不一定佩戴设备，他可能是数据分析师，或者企业的决策者。所以，好的数据内容需要一个系统的架构。如果是一个有缺陷的解决方案，可能只是满足了某一个角色在这个系统中的应用，这不是一个好的方案，没有系统性，没有完整度。\\\" [...] # 新闻资讯\\n\\n新闻资讯\\n\\n2023-06-14\\n\\n# Apple Vision Pro重新定义“远程办公” 给工业端带来无限畅想\\n\\n所有XR行业从业者都等这一刻等得太久了。\\n\\n终于，苹果在今年的WWDC发布了已经连续“跳票”数次发布会的MR眼镜Apple Vision Pro。而这款产品也真的没有让行业内外所有关注的人失望，无论是从产品的工业设计、交互体验、系统操作等各个维度，这都是一款足以让世人惊艳的产品。\\n\\n6.14apple2\\n\\nApple Vision Pro远程办公场景图\\n\\n尽管这是一款主要面向C端用户的产品，但是其中也有部分功能让大家看到了Apple Vision Pro在远程办公方面的应用。当类似于“王牌特工”中的场景真正出现在现实生活中的时候，也让大家看到了Apple Vision Pro未来在B端应用的潜在方向。\\n\\n瑞欧威尔联合创始人兼CEO李波博士，就对于Apple Vision Pro这款产品的问世，以深耕XR行业多年的亲历者角度，表达了其对于这款产品的一些不同维度的观点和看法。\\n\\n“苹果的MR眼镜已经进入到空间计算的水准，是MR眼镜中天花板级的产品。”\\n\\n在李波博士看来，苹果MR眼镜的问世，一定会带动整个行业的发展，这其中有几个维度：\\n\\n第一是对于相关供应链的推进。基于苹果的体量以及苹果对于产品质量的要求，一定会推进很多供应商支持这个项目，也就意味着未来这些供应商的资源可能也会推进关联行业的整体发展。就像我们走过的智能手机时代一样，iPhone把手机产业相关供应链能力带起来之后，所有关联行业都受益了。 [...] 足够优秀的硬件匹配足以支撑起完美用户体验的内容生态，苹果的MR眼镜的问世已经让每一位身处这个行业从业者兴奋不已，相信这会激发一场“蝴蝶效应”，推动整个XR产业的正向发展，无论是硬件产品，亦或是软件生态；无论是面对消费市场，亦或是面对企业市场。\\n\\n上一篇 强强联合！瑞欧威尔与TeamViewer全球战略合作，赋能工业一线\\n\\n下一篇 瑞欧威尔吸睛亮相“苏州智博会”工业AR+AI点燃数字革命\\n\\n电话咨询 400-8520-729\\n\\n本站使用Cookies技术用于必要的功能和分析，以便提升您的浏览体验。\\n\\n| 名称 | 域名 | 用途 | 时长 | 安全 |\\n ---  --- \\n| contact-collected | .realwear.com.cn | 下载资料 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| csrftoken | .realwear.com.cn | 数据校验 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| email-collected | .realwear.com.cn | 下载资料 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| sessionid | .realwear.com.cn | 保持会话 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| wtm | .realwear.com.cn | 隐私设置 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| wtm\\\\_id | .realwear.com.cn | 隐私设置 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n\\n#### 请输入您的联系方式\",\n        \"score\": 0.63804686,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro spatial design industrial applications\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://7t.ai/blog/apple-vision-pro-uses-for-business-spatial-video-for-any-industry/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro Uses for Business - Spatial Video for Any Industry\",\n        \"content\": \"Apple Vision Pro uses abound, the applications for this technology are expected to grow by leaps and bounds thanks to one key capability: you can capture spatial video for these VR goggles using an iPhone 15 Pro! This is a significant change from what was long the status quo: you had to hire a professional film crew to capture 3D or spatial video for use in conjunction with virtual reality headsets. And this was, as one might expect, very costly and time-consuming. In many cases, it was cost prohibitive.\\n\\nBut Apple Vision Pro and its ability to utilize footage captured on a iPhone 15 Pro means that organizations of all sizes, in all industries, with all budget sizes can now utilize virtual reality technology, making Apple Vision Pro a key component of an extended reality (XR) strategy. [...] Spatial video can be combined with artificial intelligence to generate a truly one-of-a-kind experience that allows the viewer to interact with the virtual environment. As with VR product showcases, this Apple Vision Pro use case for high-end service offerings brings optimal results when paired with an on-site virtual reality lounge, where prospective customers can experience virtual reality right there at a company’s premises.\\n\\nThis Apple Vision Pro use case is ideal for high-end service offerings, such as travel and destination marketing, vehicle customization services or the creation of bespoke designer goods. [...] Apple Vision Pro virtual reality goggles use spatial video technology — sometimes called immersive video — which creates a dynamic, three-dimensional environment for the user. This actually represents an improvement over traditional 3D video, which allows you to view a scene from a static position. If you move, the scene may become distorted. But spatial video features 6DOF (six degrees of freedom), allowing the user to move around within the environment and the surrounding digital environment shifts as your perspective shifts. This shift in perspective is the key difference between spatial video vs 3D video footage.\",\n        \"score\": 0.843393,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://eleks.com/blog/apples-vision-pro-revolutionising-industries-through-spatial-computing/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple's Vision Pro: Revolutionising Industries Through Spatial ...\",\n        \"content\": \"While it's impossible to predict the future with certainty, the advancements made in VR technology and the versatility of applications across industries make a compelling case. The potential benefits in healthcare, education, entertainment, design, and collaboration are significant.\\n\\nAs the technology continues to evolve and become more accessible, it has the potential to reshape how we interact with digital content in our daily lives.\\n\\nEmbracing the Future of Work\\n\\nApple's Vision Pro is set to redefine spatial computing and unleash its transformative potential across industries. By seamlessly blending the digital and physical worlds, this device opens up new horizons in healthcare innovations, education, and beyond. [...] Apple's Vision Pro: Revolutionising Industries Through Spatial Computing| ELEKS: Enterprise Software Development, Technology Consulting\\n\\nSkip to main content\\n\\n headsets, it showcases advanced VR capabilities that can transform various sectors.\\n\\nIn the words of the tech giant, welcome to the era of spatial computing, where Apple's Vision Pro is set to revolutionise industries such as healthcare and education.\\n\\nWhat We Know About Apple's Vision Pro\\n\\nApple Vision Prorepresents a leap forward in spatial computing, seamlessly merging digital content with the physical world. The device introduces innovative methods of interaction, utilising eye, hand, and voice commands to navigate effortlessly. [...] Vision Pro redefines how users engage with their favourite applications with an infinite canvas and the ability to scale and arrange apps anywhere. It offers a truly immersive theatre experience, brings memories to life through 3D photos and videos, facilitates meaningful collaborations, and showcases Apple's meticulous design expertise.\\n\\nImage 128: Apple's Vision Goggles in Technology Niche\\n\\nPotential Applications of VR Across Industries\\n\\n### Healthcare Innovation\\n\\nWith Apple's Vision Pro, healthcare professionals and researchers can leverage VR technology for a wide range of applications. For example, surgeons can use virtual simulations to practise complex procedures, improving their skills and reducing the risk of errors during actual surgeries.\",\n        \"score\": 0.83093774,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.persistent.com/blogs/spatial-design-designing-with-dimension-for-apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Spatial Design – Designing with Dimension for Apple Vision Pro\",\n        \"content\": \"We leverage all the available XR platforms, tools and packages to create XR experiences for different use cases across industry sectors like Healthcare, Manufacturing, Retail, Telecommunication, etc.\\n\\n      Our XR solutions cater to different challenges faced in these industries for various use cases:\\n\\n      + Operations and troubleshooting processes\\n      + Complex production processes\\n      + Field support\\n      + Different product experiences along with guidance\\n\\n      By harnessing these XR technologies, Persistent helps businesses deliver outstanding experiences which –\\n\\n      + Improve efficiency\\n      + Improve productivity\\n      + Reduce costs\\n      + Provide enhanced intuitive user interactions [...] (Image Credit Apple)\\n\\n      In our previous article, we talked about how spatial computing plays a significant role in building the Extended Reality (XR) experiences. In this article, we will talk about Apple Vision Pro – Apple’s Spatial computer and the transformative power of Apple’s visionOS in shaping the future of spatial design.\\n\\n      ###### Apple Vision Pro\\n\\n      \\n\\n      Fig 1. Apple Vision Pro headset (Image Credit Apple)\\n\\n      Launched on June 5th, 2023, Apple Vision Pro enables the blending of digital data and physical world surrounding the users, providing an interactive and immersive experience and allows users to experience Augmented Reality (AR), Mixed Reality (MR) and Virtual Reality (VR) applications. [...] Cloud & InfrastructureBusiness ApplicationsModernization & Digital TransformationIntelligent AutomationData & AnalyticsCX TransformationEnterprise Applications & IntegrationsEnterprise IT SecurityInternet of Things (IoT) About\\n\\n          Corporate ValuesLeadership TeamInvestorsEventsIn the NewsPress ReleasesAwards and RecognitionsEnvironmental, Social and GovernancePersistent FoundationDiversity and InclusionInnovation LabSheShapesAIPersistent AlumniLocationsContact Us Careers\\n           Contact Us\\n\\n      # Spatial Design – Designing with Dimension for Apple Vision Pro\\n\\n      Blog by Shilpa Ramteke, posted on November 3, 2023 in Persistent.AI\\n\\n       \\n\\n      (Image Credit Apple)\",\n        \"score\": 0.829285,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.infosys.com/services/incubating-emerging-technologies/documents/apple-vision.pdf\",\n        \"title\": \"[PDF] Apple Vision Pro and spatial computer - what it mean for enterprise ...\",\n        \"content\": \"Besides media and entertainment companies, industries poised to benefit significantly from Apple Vision Pro include: Healthcare, with applications in medical training and remote patient care Manufacturing, by enhancing processes and training through augmented reality Retail, through virtual try-on experiences and interactive displays Marketing, with immersive campaigns and product visualizations Education, by transforming learning experiences with virtual content Travel, ofering virtual exploration and augmented reality guides to enhance the tourism sector External Document © 2024 Infosys Limited External Document © 2024 Infosys Limited What Infosys is Doing in this Space Infosys set up an extended reality (XR) practice almost a decade back, which helps its clients discover meaningful use [...] VIEW POINT APPLE VISION PRO AND SPATIAL COMPUTING - WHAT IT MEANS FOR ENTERPRISES Abstract Apple Vision Pro’s launch on Feb’24 once again has brought excitement to the future of immersive experiences. At WWDC 2023, rather than pitching a futuristic, sci-fi, “Ready Player One” Metaverse type of experience, Tim Cook introduced it as Apple’s first spatial computer which instead looks at virtualizing the many screens we already encounter on a day-to-day basis (websites, movies, notes, messages, FaceTime), in an innovative and immersive way. In this article, we present our views on the recently launched Apple Vision Pro and what it means for enterprise applications, based on our prior experience and the knowledge that we have gathered by trying out the goggles first-hand. [...] Apple Current Focus and Eventual Adoption at Enterprises Apple is bringing spatial computing to the consideration of the masses in a way that makes complex technology feel approachable, simple to use, and familiar. Apple has initially positioned it for consumers, with mostly personal use cases being shown during the launch. However, Vision Pro is equally useful for designers, developers, enterprise and industry professionals. Promotional videos were also largely centered around people wearing the Vision Pro in their homes, promising something akin to playing on a big screen TV rather than a bespoke XR solution. Although the price point of $3500 is still way out of reach for most, it brings consumer adoption one step closer through better immersive experiences. Expectations are that it\",\n        \"score\": 0.77487355,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/04/apple-vision-pro-brings-a-new-era-of-spatial-computing-to-business/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro brings a new era of spatial computing to business\",\n        \"content\": \"Apple offers developers a variety of resources, including powerful APIs, rich documentation, global developer labs, Develop in Swift Tutorials, and the visionOS simulator to help companies bring game-changing Apple Vision Pro experiences to life. To further support developers, today Apple is announcing the Enterprise Spatial Design Lab, providing hands-on support from Apple to help enterprises bring apps from concept to reality. The immersive sessions will be available beginning this summer at developer.apple.com. In addition, Deloitte announced today it is expanding its Apple practice to include a new Academy for Apple Vision Pro. The practice includes more than 100 practitioners trained to deliver visionOS solutions to clients, with a series of one-week, instructor-led courses to help [...] PTC’s Onshape Vision apptransforms the way product designers and engineers view, interact with, and collaborate on complex 3D models.\\n\\nGuided Work\\n\\nGuided work requires the context of a person’s surroundings, such as a utility service technician who needs access to work orders or schematics.Resolvehas reimagined how building engineers can plan for and access information they need to make decisions about systems behind walls, including HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and fire sprinkler lines. Rather than use static paper plans, users can review high-detail plans and 3D models on Apple Vision Pro, enabling architects, builders, and maintenance workers to see, fix, and comment, enhancing the entire life cycle of a construction project. [...] PTC’s Onshape Vision apptransforms the way product designers and engineers view, interact with, and collaborate on complex 3D models.\\n\\nGuided Work\\n\\nGuided work requires the context of a person’s surroundings, such as a utility service technician who needs access to work orders or schematics.Resolvehas reimagined how building engineers can plan for and access information they need to make decisions about systems behind walls, including HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and fire sprinkler lines. Rather than use static paper plans, users can review high-detail plans and 3D models on Apple Vision Pro, enabling architects, builders, and maintenance workers to see, fix, and comment, enhancing the entire life cycle of a construction project.\",\n        \"score\": 0.76512027,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro manufacturing automotive design\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://kodytechnolab.com/blog/vision-pro-for-automotive-industry/\",\n        \"title\": \"Vision Pro for Automotive Industry: Transforming Design & ...\",\n        \"content\": \"Here is how it benefits your design process:\\n\\nUsing VisionOS in your automotive design improves innovation speed, lowers costs, and enhances product quality. Staying updated with the latest Apple Vision Pro trends ensures your business maintains a clear advantage in the market.\\n\\n## Vision Pro Use Cases in Automotive Training: Smarter, Faster, Safer\\n\\nTraining is essential to maintaining safety and quality in the automotive industry. Vision Pro technology transforms training by making it more immersive, efficient, and safe. Here’s how Vision Pro enhances key training areas:\\n\\n### Virtual Reality Driver Training for Customers [...] The automotive industry is at a pivotal moment. Vision Pro for automotive industry offers unprecedented opportunities to innovate across design, sales, training, and maintenance. If you want to stay competitive, reduce costs, and accelerate your time-to-market, embracing Vision Pro technology is no longer optional, it’s essential.\\n\\nKody Technolab, a leading VisionOS App Development Company, specializes in creating tailored, secure, and scalable Vision Pro applications for automotive businesses. Our expert team helps you navigate challenges, ensuring seamless integration and delivering solutions that maximize your ROI. [...] In summary, Vision Pro for the automotive industry drives productivity, lowers costs, and accelerates innovation across design, sales, and training. This technology supports your core business functions and helps you maintain a competitive edge in today’s automotive market.\\n\\nIf you’re looking to hire expert developers for your VisionOS projects, be sure to read our comprehensive guide, How to Hire VisionOS App Developers.\\n\\n## Redefining Automotive Design with Vision Pro for Automotive Industry\\n\\nVisionOS is revolutionizing how you design vehicles by streamlining the entire process from concept modeling to virtual validation, enabling faster, more precise, and collaborative workflows.\\n\\nadvanced automotive vr experience\\n\\nHere is how it benefits your design process:\",\n        \"score\": 0.80442166,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://manufacturingdigital.com/articles/porsche-ag-mhp-virtual-training-uses-apple-vision-pro\",\n        \"title\": \"Porsche AG & MHP Virtual Training Uses Apple Vision Pro\",\n        \"content\": \"Article\\n\\nSmart Manufacturing\\n\\n# Porsche AG & MHP Virtual Training Uses Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nByRachael Brown\\n\\nMay 17, 2024\\n\\nundefined mins\\n\\nShare\\n\\nShare\\n\\nMarkus Wambach, COO and Member of the Management Board at MHP\\n\\nMHP and Porsche AG have been using 3D training to upskill production line staff, addressing the digital skills gap in supply chain manufacturing\\n\\nLeading automotive manufacturer Porsche has partnered with management and IT consultancy MHP to deliver innovative augmented reality training solutions.\\n\\nOn 2 February, 2024, the Apple Vision Pro was released, with major commercial and industry applications. Like Epson’s smart glasses, the futuristic headset can be utilised to bring interactivity and realism to employee training exercises without real-world costs or risks. [...] The long-term goal of both companies is to formally implement the Apple Vision Pro as a means to train and educate employees for production. The solution has the potential to revolutionise other areas, including after-sales in the automotive industry.\\n\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\nMake sure you check out the latest edition of Manufacturing Digital and also sign up to our global conference series - Procurement & Supply Chain 2024 & Sustainability LIVE 2024  \\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\  \\nManufacturing Digital is a BizClik brand.\\n\\n## Company portals\\n\\n \\n\\n  ### MHP – A Porsche Company\\n \\n\\n  ### Porsche\\n\\n## Tags\\n\\nApplePorsche AGMHPtrainingaugmented reality [...] To demonstrate the effectiveness of the Apple Vision Pro, a showcase event was held in partnership with Porsche at its Zuffenhausen plant in Germany. Part of the plant's production process was completed using the headsets' realistic 3D training, and CAD data of a welding rotary table and manufacturing robot was realistically mapped in a “shop floor training” session.\\n\\nThe employee saw the entire task laid out, step by step, inside the headset alongside repair instructions superimposed on a 3D model. This process increased employee satisfaction and reduced errors, with options for assessment and certification.\\n\\nWhat users see whilst training in the Apple Vision Pro\",\n        \"score\": 0.7395922,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/alexlevin/2025/04/24/porsches-new-apple-vision-pro-app-lets-you-design-your-dream-911/\",\n        \"title\": \"Porsche's New Apple Vision Pro App Lets You Design Your Dream ...\",\n        \"content\": \"More broadly, as luxury brands across various sectors – including fashion houses like Gucci, luggage makers such as Rimowa, jewelers like Bulgari, and automotive manufacturers – experiment with the Apple Vision Pro, spatial computing and XR devices as customer touchpoints, legitimate questions arise concerning the genuine value proposition versus the potential for expensive novelties. [...] Ultimately, while questions of immediate utility versus novelty arise in the context of consumer-facing automotive applications of spatial computing, it’s important to acknowledge that this technology has already proven its value as a significant tool in the design world. Across architecture, interior design, and for global design teams collaborating on product development, spatial computing offers tangible benefits in visualization, collaboration, and efficiency. This established utility in the design and creation process provides a crucial context as automotive brands explore its potential as a new customer touchpoint.\\n\\nAn Impending Spatial Computing Race [...] Porsche's New Apple Vision Pro App Lets You Design Your Dream 911\\n\\n\\n\\ndpa/picture alliance via Getty Images\\n\\nPorsche has launched its \\\"911 Spirit 70\\\" app for Apple Vision Pro, marking the luxury automaker’s first significant foray into customer-facing spatial computing. The new application, available today on the Vision Pro App Store, allows users to place a virtual Porsche 911 in their physical environment, examine it from all angles, and customize it in real-time.\\n\\nImage 2: Screen capture from the \\\"911 Spirit 70\\\" app for Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nScreen capture from the \\\"911 Spirit 70\\\" app for Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nDr. Ing. h.c. F. Porsche AG\",\n        \"score\": 0.73778254,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro for Business\",\n        \"content\": \"# The future of business starts with vision.\\n\\nSpatial Analogue shown in video\\n\\nCAE mobile immersive training shown in video\\n\\nVisage Ease VP\\\\ shown in video\\n\\nPorsche Car Configurator shown in video\\n\\nApple Vision Pro reinvents what’s possible for business, opening up completely new ways to work. Teams can collaborate in spatial workspaces, streamline workflows, train efficiently, and create incredible customer experiences. From manufacturing to healthcare and beyond, spatial computing with Apple Vision Pro can transform entire industries.\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Redesign the design process.\\n\\n3DLive\\\\\\n\\n### Speed through reviews. [...] ### Demos shoppers can see — and feel.\\n\\nDeliver immersive product demos that help shoppers configure, try, and buy products like never before. At Porsche, customers personalize their dream cars in life size with Apple Vision Pro and experience them in a vivid, delightful way.\\n\\nA customer in a Porsche showroom wearing Apple Vision Pro views a 3D projection of a sportscar and talks with an employee\\nA customer in a Porsche showroom wearing Apple Vision Pro views a 3D projection of a sportscar and talks with an employee\\n\\n### Elevating customer exploration.\\n\\nBuild engaging experiences like augmented interior designs, virtual product try-ons, and visuals placed in real-life environments. And with the JigSpace app, manufacturing leaders like EVAPCO can transform customer education.\",\n        \"score\": 0.72042775,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"http://www.designlife-cycle.com/apple-vision-pro\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro - Design Life-Cycle\",\n        \"content\": \"The production of AR lenses for the Apple Vision Pro begins with the extraction of raw materials. The primary materials include silica, silicon, and various rare earth elements, which are essential for manufacturing microchips and other electronic components. The extraction process itself is resource-intensive, requiring substantial amounts of water and energy. For instance, silicon, a key component, is derived from silica found in sand. The refining process of silicon is energy-intensive, involving high-temperature furnaces that consume large amounts of electricity, predominantly sourced from fossil fuels . During manufacturing, the production of microchips for AR lenses generates significant waste and emissions. Mining of these materials is energy-intensive and leads to significant [...] The Apple Vision Pro is a brand new spatial computing device released by Apple in 2024. This device is worn as a headset and weaves reality with a digital landscape to create a unique user experience. The Vision Pro captures reality through its many cameras and displays it to the user through screens. This report aims to detail the life cycle of these components. The life cycle of the Apple Vision Pro's cameras involve the acquisition and processing of raw materials. The introduction of raw materials is most heavily involved in their acquisition and processing steps, but some new materials must also be introduced in distribution, maintenance, recycling, and waste. All of the materials used at every step will be accounted for in this life cycle analysis.\",\n        \"score\": 0.70799106,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Vision Pro CAD 3D modeling industrial use\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.onshape.com/en/blog/apple-vision-pro-cad-app-use-cases\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro and Product Design: 4 Practical Use Cases\",\n        \"content\": \"### INDUSTRY SOLUTIONS\\n\\nEliminate inefficiencies of traditional product development, no matter what industry. From concept to production, teams using Onshape gain the agility and control they need to innovate without compromise.\\n\\n### Aerospace & Defense\\n\\n### Automotive\\n\\n### Consumer Products\\n\\n### Education\\n\\n### Electronics\\n\\n### Energy\\n\\n### Government\\n\\n### Machine Design\\n\\n### Medical Devices\\n\\n### Robotics\\n\\n### Startups\\n\\nSign In Arrow\\n\\nDownload the Onshape Mobile App\\n\\nBlog Hero Image\\n\\n# Apple Vision Pro and Product Design: 4 Practical Use Cases\\n\\nauthor image\\n\\nThe integration of the Onshape Vision app with Apple Vision Pro represents a significant leap forward in spatial computing, offering engineers and designers a more intuitive and interactive way to visualize and manipulate 3D models. [...] Here’s a closer look at how this technology can transform your design and review processes.\\n\\n## Onshape Vision: Bridging the Gap Between Digital and Physical\\n\\nOnshape Vision leverages the spatial computing capabilities of Apple Vision Pro to bring a new level of immersion to 3D CAD models.\\n\\nThe app bridges Onshape’s CAD & PDM mobile platform running on an Apple iPad or iPhone with Apple Vision Pro’s headset, empowering users to interact with parts and assemblies in a way that's both intuitive and realistic.\\n\\nImagine scaling an assembly to fit on your desk, grabbing components with your hands, rotating them, and inspecting them from any angle. This is spatial computing in action: enhancing the review and inspection of digital designs by situating them within the physical world. [...] Example: Service technicians use Onshape Vision to interact with a 3D model of bespoke heavy equipment in a training session. This immersive experience allows them to familiarize themselves with the customer's specific model, discussing and practicing maintenance procedures in a virtual environment that mimics actual conditions.\\n\\n### Exploring Customization and Personalization Options\\n\\nBenefit: Offers customers a unique, interactive experience to explore and visualize customization options, leading to increased satisfaction and confidence in their purchase decisions.\",\n        \"score\": 0.7752821,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro for Business\",\n        \"content\": \"### Train teams smarter, wherever they are.\\n\\nProvide immersive, true-to-life training on key equipment anytime, anywhere. Industry leaders like CAE use Apple Vision Pro to train pilots in detailed simulations, leading to better retention for full-scale simulator sessions.1\\n\\nA person's hand ajusts a control knob in a 3D projection of a plane's cockpit\\nA person's hand ajusts a control knob in a 3D projection of a plane's cockpit\\n\\n### Bring a new perspective to learning.\\n\\nEasily instruct and simplify learning with lifelike 3D experiences. Apps like Complete HeartX help medical students explore anatomy in stunning detail using photorealistic models, videos, and simulations. [...] ### Get on the same page, product, or prototype.\\n\\nProduct designers can easily collaborate and review CAD models together with onsite and remote teams. Using PTC’s Onshape Vision app, stakeholders get real-time access to models and components in an immersive workspace.\\n\\nA 3D projection of a CAD model of machinery and information about the machinery, projected into an office room\\nA 3D projection of a CAD model of machinery and information about the machinery, projected into an office room\\n\\n## Immersive Training\\n\\n### Simulated training. Real results.\\n\\nBILT 3D Immersive Instructions\\\\\\n\\n### Train teams smarter, wherever they are. [...] A 3D projection of an EVAPCO Cooling Tower in an industrial space, with controls to flip through information about the tower\\nA 3D projection of an EVAPCO Cooling Tower in an industrial space, with controls to flip through information about the tower\\n\\n### Showcase products without the setup.\\n\\nCustomers can see, explore, and step inside products virtually. Decathlon’s custom app lets shoppers interact with true-to-scale outdoor equipment without opening a box.\\n\\nA 3D projection of a camping tent overlaid in a sporting goods showroom, and a floating window shows additional product information\\nA 3D projection of a camping tent overlaid in a sporting goods showroom, and a floating window shows additional product information\\n\\n## Productivity\\n\\n### Infinite workspace. Ultimate workflow.\",\n        \"score\": 0.74004334,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.shapr3d.com/products/vision-os\",\n        \"title\": \"CAD on Vision Pro | Meet Shapr3D Spatial CAD\",\n        \"content\": \"iPadOS\\n\\n or later\\n\\nInstallation guide\\n\\nContact sales\\n\\nA few details now.  \\nA tailored solution next.\\n\\n# Shapr3D for apple vision pro\\n\\nNow enable real-time 3D design and editing directly on the Vision Pro, equipping your team with precise 3D communication and collaboration in the immersive environment of Spatial Computer-Aided Design.\\n\\nStart modelingSign upRequest a demo\\n\\n## See how enterprises collaborate on the only CAD to run natively on Apple Vision Pro.\\n\\n## Reduce Reliance on Costly Physical Prototypes\\n\\nReduce the amount of expensive physical prototypes that are needed in the process of designing and manufacturing a product. With Shapr3D on Vision Pro, you can create fully editable digital prototypes that allow for quick adjustments without committing to physical builds. [...] Two people talking, one of them is wearing an Apple Vision Pro headset viewing a 3D model\\n\\n## An immersive design solution, like no other.\\n\\n### Unparalleled Visual Quality.\\n\\nHarness the unbeatable visual detail and clarity of Apple Vision Pro.\\n\\n### powered by parasolid®\\n\\nWork between any CAD system and craft precise, manufacturing-ready models.\\n\\n## Integral part of the Shapr3D ecosystem.\\n\\nStart modelingSign up [...] EnterpriseProductResources\\nPricing\\n\\nR&D and design\\n\\nConceptual designDesign reviewDigital validation (XR)\\n\\nProduct engineering\\n\\nPrototypingPeer reviewMechanism designSimulation preprocessing\\n\\nManufacturing engineering\\n\\nTool and equipment designAssembly planning in XRDFM review\\n\\nManufacturing ops\\n\\nMaintenance and repairContinuous improvementJig, fixture and end of tool arm tooling designManufacturing tool retrofittingErgonomics testing\\n\\nSales and marketing\\n\\nProject management and Sales\\n\\nFast concepts\\n\\nMultiple devicesCAD toolsAdaptive User InterfaceSiemens Parasolid Kernel\\n\\nCollaborative design\\n\\nShared team spaceBrowser-based review linksFlexible Cloud Storage\\n\\nIntegrated XR\\n\\nReal-time visualizationAR: Core workflow, not a pluginNative on Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nCAD integrations\",\n        \"score\": 0.6654328,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.engineering.com/should-engineers-buy-the-apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Should engineers buy the Apple Vision Pro?\",\n        \"content\": \"“We were excited to get an early look of the Apple Vision Pro,” Greg Brown, vice president of product management for Onshape at PTC, told Engineering.com. “We knew that because of the way that it was going to come out—the functionality, the ease of use and all of these things—the barriers that were previously there in doing this type of visualization would be addressed in a major way.”\\n\\nBrown views the biggest current engineering uses for the Vision Pro as ideation, collaboration, and evaluation, and says these are the areas where the Onshape app has focused first. The current app allows multiple people to interact with a model in the same virtual space. The following video from PTC shows the app in action: [...] ### Apple Vision Pro beyond design\\n\\nEngineering work extends far beyond 3D models, and companies are testing out VR and AR software for use on the manufacturing floor, construction sites and beyond.\\n\\nView from within the Apple Vision Pro Resolve app showing a comment left within a building. (Image: Resolve.) [...] PTC has hinted at plans to bring 3D design tools to the Vision Pro as well, but right now their software is focused on display, rendering and commenting.\\n\\nHungarian CAD provider Shapr3D also offers its 3D design software on the Vision Pro, but the immersive version of the software aims to be much more versatile than mere viewing. The company is offering demos of their Vision Pro software which advertises the ability to design fully in the headset.\\n\\nOther engineering software available for the Apple Vision Pro includes Nvidia Omniverse, which can stream data and applications on the headset; Vectary, an interactive product visualizer; Graphisoft’s BIMx presentation app; and JigSpace, a 3D presentation app.\\n\\n### Apple Vision Pro beyond design\",\n        \"score\": 0.63939893,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://poly.cam/vision-pro\",\n        \"title\": \"Native 3D App & 3D Models for Apple Vision Pro - Polycam\",\n        \"content\": \"### Your own 3D sandbox\\n\\nCapture your own environment or find one in our library, then fill it with 3D objects of your choosing. Mix and match different captures and models to your heart's content. Renovate your home, re-imagine your surroundings, or assemble your very own 3D collage - the only limit is your imagination.\\n\\n### Take the next step in immersive 3D.\\n\\nDownload now on the App Store.\\n\\nDownload on the\\n\\nApp Store\\n\\nImage of Apple Vision Pro headset\\n\\n#### Browse 3D models\\n\\nAnatomyDinosaursArchitectureFoodSneakersVehiclesLegoAutoCAD modelsMaya modelsFBX modelsGLTF modelsUnity modelsBlender modelsUnreal engine models\\n\\nOil & gasReal estateHealth careRetail & E-commerseSolar & Renewable energyForensics & Law Enforcement\\n\\nUse case\\n\\nFacilities managementStructural design\\n\\nResources\",\n        \"score\": 0.62633044,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14948,"aggregated":"[\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro industrial design case study 2024 2025\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.scribd.com/document/864576806/Apple-Vision-Pro-Development-A-Case-Study\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro Development A Case Study | PDF - Scribd\",\n        \"content\": \"The Apple Vision Pro, introduced in 2024, represents a watershed momentin spatial computing that transcends conventional boundaries o augmentedand virtual reality. This case study presents a comprehensive analysis o the device’s journey rom conceptualization through commercialization, ex-amining the intricate interplay o research breakthroughs, design iterations,and strategic decisions that shaped its development. Through investiga-tion o patent portolios, technical documentation, and industry analyses, wetrace how Apple’s decade-long investment in undamental technologies—rommicro-OLED displays and eye-tracking systems to the custom-designed M2and R1 silicon architecture—culminated in this ambitious product. Thestudy delves deep into critical phases o product development, [...] Apple, Apple Vision Pro, Augmented Reality (AR), VirtualReality (VR), Product Design, Innovation\\n\\nPreprint submitted to Elsevier January 4, 2025\\n\\nDownload to read ad-free\\n\\nApple Vision Pro: A Privacy Overview\\n\\nFrom Scribd3 pages70 views\\n\\nApple Vision Pro: A Privacy Overview\\n\\nNo ratings yet\\n\\n1. Introduction [...] 15 pages\\n Exploring VR and AR Technologies\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Exploring VR and AR Technologies\\n\\n  3 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro Product Overview\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Apple Vision Pro Product Overview\\n\\n  2 pages\\n Apple Product Innovations 2024-2025\\n\\n  \\n\\n  100% (1)\\n\\n  Apple Product Innovations 2024-2025\\n\\n  282 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro: Future of AR Technology\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Apple Vision Pro: Future of AR Technology\\n\\n  13 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro Report\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Apple Vision Pro Report\\n\\n  16 pages\\n Future Computing Trends and Innovations\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Future Computing Trends and Innovations\\n\\n  3 pages\\n Advancements in HCI Technologies\\n\\n  \\n\\n  No ratings yet\\n\\n  Advancements in HCI Technologies\\n\\n  10 pages\\n Apple Vision Pro Marketing Insights\",\n        \"score\": 0.82895297,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@jlacuna1031/case-history-of-apples-vision-pro-development-process-implementation-9448b715e0d0\",\n        \"title\": \"Case History of Apple's Vision Pro Development Process ... - Medium\",\n        \"content\": \"Sitemap\\n\\nOpen in app\\n\\nSign in\\n\\nSign in\\n\\n# Case History of Apple’s Vision Pro Development Process & Implementation\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\n4 min readNov 6, 2025\\n\\nDeveloping a new product and bringing it to market is neither particularly fast nor easy; most companies have a process for doing so, often a variation of the New Product Development (NPD) process. A great example in the real world is Apple and its recent release of the headset Vision Pro. To an outsider, it may seem that Apple simply decided to create this product one day, but in reality, a lengthy process brought it from a thought to customers’ hands.\\n\\n## Idea Generation [...] ## Get Jose Acuna’s stories in your inbox\\n\\nJoin Medium for free to get updates from this writer.\\n\\nReferences\\n\\n-Apple Inc. (2024, June 5). Introducing Apple Vision Pro: Apple’s first spatial computer. Apple Newsroom. \\n\\n-Robertson, A. (2023, June 5). Apple Vision Pro is Apple’s new $3,499 AR headset. The Verge. \\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\n## Written by Jose Acuna\\n\\n0 followers\\n\\n·1 following\\n\\n## No responses yet\\n\\nWrite a response\\n\\nWhat are your thoughts?\\n\\n## More from Jose Acuna\\n\\nHow Starbucks Uses Marketing to Connect With People Everywhere\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\nJose Acuna\\n\\n## How Starbucks Uses Marketing to Connect With People Everywhere\\n\\n### Before this marketing class, I did not think about how much strategy goes into something as simple as buying coffee. After reading Chapters…\\n\\nOct 24, 2025\",\n        \"score\": 0.79522943,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.aalpha.net/articles/apple-vision-pro-use-cases-and-applications/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro Use Cases and Applications 2025 - Aalpha\",\n        \"content\": \"Furthermore, the product is more versatile and gives users an incredible feeling of innovation and realism. With these great innovative features, Apple Vision Pro serves well in refining prototypes, sketching designs, and 3D modeling.\\n\\n ## Education\\n\\nEducation is another crucial sector that has grown thanks to Apple Vision Pro. Users have seen a more engaging and innovative education process with the product. With the tool, it is more accessible to actualize distance learning. Surprisingly, users can have multiple distance learning sessions all at once. The tool has more significant support for e-learning and teleconferencing, among others. [...] ## Entertainment and social space\\n\\nThe entertainment and social space is more welcoming and appealing, thanks to Apple Vision Pro. It comes with high-quality displays, support for spatial audio, and anything entertaining any user would love to experience. With Vision Pro, expect to immerse yourself in a theater-like experience in the living spaces. Its features allow synchronized viewing for a better and more compelling experience. [...] ## Innovativeness and productiveness\\n\\nApple Vision Pro has a three-dimensional, flexible, innovative, and productive interface. With such an interface, users can easily access the productive right anywhere. The innovative device allows you to maneuver between a range of supported screens easily. Surprisingly, all these happen simultaneously, giving the users an even better experience. With such a better experience, users can easily organize their virtual space even through voice inputs. With the seamless and intuitive experience, users enjoy a productive environment free from disruption, thus enabling faster and easier completion of tasks. The multitasking support makes the experience much better.\",\n        \"score\": 0.7795405,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.idc.com/resource-center/blog/apple-vision-pro-2025-with-m5-a-sharper-vision-for-spatial-computing/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro (2025) with M5: A Sharper Vision for Spatial ... - IDC\",\n        \"content\": \"Siri also continues to lag. In a world where AI assistants are becoming more conversational and context-aware, Apple’s voice interface feels dated. With competitors integrating advanced AI into their headsets, Apple needs to accelerate its efforts here to stay competitive.\\n\\n## Final Thoughts\\n\\nThe 2025 Vision Pro is less of a radical reinvention and more thoughtful refinement. Apple didn’t need to push the tech forward, but it did. And in doing so, it’s made the device more comfortable, more powerful, and more developer-friendly.\\n\\nFor businesses and developers, these changes matter. The M5 chip unlocks new possibilities, the Dual Knit Band improves day-to-day usability, and the continued focus on performance ensures the Vision Pro remains a leader in spatial computing. [...] ## A Subtle but Significant Upgrade\\n\\nAt first glance, the 2025 Vision Pro doesn’t scream “new.” The design remains familiar, and the core experience is still rooted in spatial computing. But the changes Apple has made are thoughtful and impactful.\\n\\nThe most immediately noticeable improvement is the new Dual Knit Band. Comfort has long been a sticking point for head-mounted devices, and Apple’s solution here is elegant. The new band distributes weight more evenly, reduces pressure points, and makes long sessions far more tolerable. It’s a small change that dramatically improves usability for users who wear the headset for hours at a time.\\n\\n## M5: Power, Efficiency, and AI Muscle [...] Skip to main Skip to search Skip to footer\\n\\nBecome a Client\\n\\nBecome a Client\\n\\nTechnologies   October 23, 2025  5 min\\n\\n# Apple Vision Pro (2025) with M5: A Sharper Vision for Spatial Computing\\n\\nShare on LinkedIn   Share on X%20with%20M5:%20A%20Sharper%20Vision%20for%20Spatial%20Computing)\\n\\nApple’s Vision Pro was already a technological marvel when it launched. With its ultra-high-resolution displays, spatial audio, and seamless integration into Apple’s ecosystem, it set a new benchmark for mixed reality. But in 2025, Apple chose not to rest on its laurels. The updated Vision Pro, now powered by the M5 chip, refines the experience in meaningful ways especially for the professionals and developers who rely on it most.\\n\\n## A Subtle but Significant Upgrade\",\n        \"score\": 0.76279575,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://augmentedenterprisesummit.com/looking-back-at-the-most-notable-xr-use-cases-of-2024/\",\n        \"title\": \"Looking Back at the Most Notable XR Use Cases of 2024\",\n        \"content\": \"Though Apple’s headset failed to meet industrial enterprise needs, healthcare and medical professionals proved to be big fans. In breakthrough experiments, Apple Vision Pro assisted in spinal and heart surgeries at London’s Cromwell Hospital and Stanford Health Care in the Bay Area (March) as well as in dozens of surgeries at India’s GEM Hospital in Chennai (May). In all cases, Vision Pro provided consolidated, hands-free access to real-time information about the patient and procedure. \\n\\nMeanwhile, Sharp Healthcare in San Diego established a Spatial Computing Center of Excellence and purchased 30 Apple Vision Pro headsets for workers doing “all sorts of jobs,” and Boston Children’s Hospital created a medical personnel training app for the Vision Pro. [...] Related: Apple Vision Pro: Already a Hit in Healthcare and Retail\\n\\nThe medical industry displayed interest in XR in general, as well: Boston’s Mass General Brigham tested XR for code cart training of new nurses, while surgeons from several departments established the UC Davis Medical Extended Reality (MXR) Research Group.\\n\\n2024 also saw rising interest and even concrete use cases from the public sector, including federal agencies and local governments. Most recently, the U.S. Department of Labor’s Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) expanded its use of Vuzix M400 smart glasses with the aim of reducing response times, improving operational efficiency, and boosting workplace safety. [...] Share\\n\\nShare\\n\\n2024 Enterprise Use Case Trends:\\n\\n –Greater interest in XR from healthcare and the public sector\\n –Training still the top XR application in enterprise (increasingly in combo with AI)\\n –Digital twins are expanding to more and more industries\\n –More reporting of quantifiable ROI\\n –Sustainability as a frequently cited driving factor and benefit of XR\\n –Up-and-coming use cases: PR and employee wellness\\n\\n## Retail, Healthcare, and Government\\n\\nLet’s start with Apple Vision Pro. Vision Pro arrived in February of this year, and numerous brands created apps for the spatial computer. These included popular retailers like Wayfair (Decorify interior design app), J. Crew (Virtual Closet), Lowe’s (Style Studio), and Best Buy (Envision to plan your home technology setup).\",\n        \"score\": 0.7279179,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro 工业设计 案例\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://pdf.dfcfw.com/pdf/H3_AP202312281615148585_1.pdf\",\n        \"title\": \"[PDF] 苹果Vision Pro 硬件顶级配置，内容生态不断搭建\",\n        \"content\": \"Room 采用 Unity 引擎制作， VisionOS 通过与 RealityKit 的深度集成来支持该引擎。 图29：Rec Room 被Vision Pro 列入“我们喜爱的应用程序和游戏” 资料来源：UploadVR，信达证券研发中心 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  18 图30： Rec Room 在Vision Pro 上进行测试 资料来源：UploadVR，信达证券研发中心 Vision Pro 应用行业——工业领域 随着工业数字化转型、工业4.0、智能制造等概念的推广，越来越多的企业开始寻求智能化的工业技术升级， 希望以技术赋能产业，为企业创造新的价值。具体应用环节例如：产品设计、生产制造、巡检维修等。工业产 品设计时可以将想法以全息影像形式立体呈现，缩短开发周期多维度感知设计效果。生产制造环节，MR 技术 可以让用户即刻看到数字影像与真实环境融合的效果，利用MR 技术可即刻查看到工作场景中各个相关线路、 管道及其详细的测量值，并能够高精准度地进行安装、搭建。在工业生产环境中，工作人员也可以戴上MR 眼 镜进行巡检及时准确的发现生产故障。 图31：MR 在工业领域中的应用 资料来源：东孚科技，信达证券研发中心 Vision Pro 应用行业——医疗行业 MR 应用在医疗领域，具体在外科医学教育、医学临床、远程协作及手术导航等细分赛道，有望为新一轮智慧 手术的技术迭代带来新的创新驱动因子。锦瑟医疗通过MR 技术，可以将平面的影像学检查图像重建成3D 数 字模型，投射到手术室的空间中，与真实场景中的患者情况相融合，进而辅助医生实现术前手术规划、手术路 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  19 径模拟、术中辅助定位等，以提高手术的精准性、安全性和成功率。早在2019 年，锦瑟医疗就取得国内第一 张基于混合现实技术的产品注册证。 图32： MR [...] ➢ Pancake 光学方案：Pancake 方案可以折叠光路，从而实现轻薄。Quest 3 使用了2P 的Pancake 方案 并且树立了较高的专利壁垒，苹果采用了3P Pancake 设计，这种方案的优势体现在性能，劣势则在于工 艺和成本。 ➢ 虹膜识别：人的虹膜是唯一的，在出生之后不久便会定型，成长的过程中很难发生改变。苹果搭载了虹 膜识别方案，称为Optic ID。我们也非常看好这一项技术，可以预见，在国内腾讯和海外苹果推动之下， 虹膜识别技术有望快速在VRAR 设备乃至手机等终端迅速普及。 ➢ IPD 调节：Vision Pro 能够自动检测用户的瞳距，并调节两个显示屏的距离，让用户获得最佳视觉体验。 为了满足近视人群需求，苹果还与蔡司合作定制了光学镜片。 ➢ 空间音频：位于耳朵两侧的双驱动单元音频组件能带来沉浸式的空间音频体验。Vision Pro 还能分析空间 的特征和材质，使声音精确匹配物理时空。 此外，苹果还有许多不同程度的创新，例如一整块以 3D 方式成型与压层的玻璃，表面进行光学抛光，用作一 系列摄像头和传感器的镜片，将数字内容与真实世界完美融合。轻质眼罩使用柔软的织物，提供各种尺寸和 形状以适合每一位用户的脸型。可调节松紧的边带确保音频保持靠近用户的耳朵，采用 3D 织法的多种尺寸的 头带不仅舒适、透气且具有弹性。头带透过单一机制固定，容易更换尺寸及造型。 图8：苹果Vision Pro Pancake 光学方案 图9：虹膜识别 资料来源：VR 陀螺，信达证券研发中心 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 图10：Vision Pro 空间音频 图11：Vision Pro 绑带 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  9 [...] EyeSight 反向透视 售价 3499 美元 发售时间 2024 年年初 资料来源：VR 陀螺，信达证券研发中心 硬件端阵容豪华，传感器搭建数字世界感知现实的桥梁。苹果展现出与竞争对手完全不同的路线，在显示、眼 动追踪、手势交互等方面，为了追求良好的效果，苹果Vision Pro 硬件阵容强大，以传感器为例，Vision Pro 搭 载了12 个摄像头、5 个传感器（1 个Lidar、2 个结构光深度传感、2 个IR 传感）和6 个麦克风。 Vision Pro 正面有 2 个主摄像头、4 个向下的摄像头、2 个侧面摄像头。1 个激光雷达分布在中央，两侧各有一 个原深感摄像头，还有两个IR 照明器。在Vision Pro 内侧，有四个红外摄像头和两个LED 补光，主要用于眼 动追踪。 以红外摄像头为例，苹果左右各配备了2 颗红外摄像头，在保障追踪精度的同时，还能测算双眼瞳深，进而实 现更好的画面显示效果，而对手大多只配备一颗。这项技术并不是一项新技术，而出现这种结果，是因为苹果 的Vision Pro 在设计的时候一直以用户作为根本出发点，没有陷入卷成本的“高级游戏机”漩涡。 请阅读最后一页免责声明及信息披露  6 图6：Vision Pro 传感器分布 资料来源：苹果官网，信达证券研发中心 苹果Vision Pro 主显示屏采用Micro OLED，单眼分辨率达到4K，这是目前市场上首次出现的使用Micro OLED 实现双目8K 效果的产品。Micro OLED 显示屏具有自发光、能耗低和体积小等特性，可实现更高色域、 分辨率及发光效率等优势，天然适配于近眼显示设备。Micro OLED 采用单晶硅晶圆为背板，接近半导体工艺， 而为了获得更大FOV，需要更大的屏幕支撑，而在屏幕尺寸变大的过程中，除了制造工艺、成本等直线大幅上\",\n        \"score\": 0.80442166,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com.cn/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro 商务应用- Apple (中国大陆)\",\n        \"content\": \"### 借助数字孪生，获取精准指导。\\n\\n在实物旁边，放置一个精细的模型进行对照，还可使用数码分步操作指南，来进一步提升工作效率。有了 BILT 3D Immersive Instructions app，建筑和水电等领域的专业技师能更快、更准确、也更安全地完成工作。\\n\\n一只手将接有电线的机械盒安装在墙上，旁边有 3D 成像的同款设备。\\n一只手将接有电线的机械盒安装在墙上，旁边有 3D 成像的同款设备。\\n\\n## 顾客体验\\n\\n### 吸引顾客， 从心动到行动。\\n\\n劳氏公司 (Lowe’s) 风格工作室\\n\\n### 产品演示看得真实，感受真切。\\n\\n提供沉浸式的产品演示，让顾客以耳目一新的方式配置、试用和购买产品。在保时捷，顾客可使用 Apple Vision Pro，以真实尺寸个性定制梦想座驾，还能以生动愉悦的方式尽情体验。\\n\\n保时捷展厅内，一位佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的顾客一边观看 3D 成像的跑车，一边与工作人员交谈。\\n保时捷展厅内，一位佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的顾客一边观看 3D 成像的跑车，一边与工作人员交谈。\\n\\n### 吸引顾客了解更多，体验更好。\\n\\n以增强现实效果呈现室内设计、提供虚拟产品试用，以及在真实环境中加入视觉特效，众多引人入胜的新方式，带来精彩纷呈的客户体验。借助 JigSpace app，Evapco 等制造业龙头能全面革新客户教育的模式。\\n\\n一间工业厂房中，一个 3D 投影的 EVAPCO 冷却塔，旁边有关于冷却塔的信息可翻阅。\\n一间工业厂房中，一个 3D 投影的 EVAPCO 冷却塔，旁边有关于冷却塔的信息可翻阅。\\n\\n### 无需搭建，产品精彩呈现。\\n\\n顾客能以虚拟的方式欣赏、研究，甚至深入探索产品的内部设计。通过迪卡侬的自定 app，顾客无需打开包装盒，就能体验真实比例的户外装备。 [...] # 放眼新境， 远见企业未来。\\n\\nSpatial Analogue shown in video\\n\\nCAE shown in video\\n\\nVisage Ease VP shown in video\\n\\nPorsche Car Configurator shown in video\\n\\nApple Vision Pro 开启商务应用的无限可能，解锁全然一新的工作方式。团队可在别开生面的工作空间中相互协作、优化工作流程、提升培训效率，并创造一流的客户体验。从制造业、医疗行业，到更广阔的领域，借助 Apple Vision Pro 的空间计算能力，各行各业都能突破革新。\\n\\n## 设计\\n\\n### 设计流程， 彻底重新设计。\\n\\n3DLive\\n\\n### 加快评估进度。\\n\\n无需制作实体样品，就能与世界各地的团队共同审核原型设计，从而加快工作流程。通过 Spatial Analogue 这类 app，相关的各方均可参与其中，还可使用各种空间配件在虚拟物体上标注与绘图。\\n\\n一位头戴 Apple Vision Pro 的设计师，通过手的移动对一把 3D 成像的椅子进行测量。\\n一位头戴 Apple Vision Pro 的设计师，通过手的移动对一把 3D 成像的椅子进行测量。\\n\\n### 细节全面看通透。\\n\\n全球团队都能通过分层 3D 模型，从各个角度查看内部零件。有了 Innoactive 这样的平台，大众汽车等企业能借助视觉化的数码模型，来评估汽车零部件，从而简化设计流程。\\n\\n一只手做出捏合的手势，与 3D 成像的汽车动力传动系统进行互动。\\n一只手做出捏合的手势，与 3D 成像的汽车动力传动系统进行互动。\\n\\n### 空间设计，重塑零售空间。 [...] ### 快速上手，顺畅上岗。\\n\\n通过各种培训单元，帮助员工减少失误，提升学习速度，尽快准备就绪。在荷兰皇家航空公司，技术人员会使用 Engine Shop app，将操作指南叠加在真实比例的大型设备模型上，随后按步骤进行操作。\\n\\n一间工业厂房中，有一个 3D 成像的喷气发动机，另有一个浮窗，显示一系列操作步骤。\\n一间工业厂房中，有一个 3D 成像的喷气发动机，另有一个浮窗，显示一系列操作步骤。\\n\\n### 更低成本，更快精通机械。\\n\\n员工在修理、操作和维护实体设备时，能将所需信息叠加进空间，从而快速掌握大量资讯。ThingLink 可将教程与组件详情直接叠加在机械设备上，一切都一目了然。\\n\\n仓库中的一台大型机械，旁边有一个 3D 成像的窗口，写着“Key Features of the Sabi EB 250”的字样。\\n仓库中的一台大型机械，旁边有一个 3D 成像的窗口，写着“Key Features of the Sabi EB 250”的字样。\\n\\n## 工作指导\\n\\n### 专业指导， 专攻复杂项目。\\n\\nVisage Ease VP\\n\\n### 上手操作设备，说明书不用在手上。\\n\\n员工无需手持说明书，也能浏览数码参考资料，双手都能专注在工作上，令准确度与速度双双提升。在荷兰皇家航空公司，技术人员使用 Engine Shop app 来确定扭矩序列，确保安装顺利无误。\\n\\n飞机库中，一名佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的技术人员使用手中的工具，调整飞机的挡风玻璃。\\n飞机库中，一名佩戴 Apple Vision Pro 的技术人员使用手中的工具，调整飞机的挡风玻璃。\\n\\n### 借助数字孪生，获取精准指导。\",\n        \"score\": 0.78944516,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.easemob.com/news/10391\",\n        \"title\": \"Vision Pro 的8 年历程：只有苹果才能这样造产品- 环信\",\n        \"content\": \"堪比 SpaceX 造火箭的投入，只为了解决一些特别基础的需求：\\n\\n 让设备更轻。目前较轻的头戴设备一般 400~500 克。苹果一度提出过 150g 重的头戴设备方案，目标是让人连续佩戴 8 小时。但苹果并没有透露 Vision Pro 的重量，只是强调用了更轻的材料，比如用透气的织物做头带、外接电池。\\n 让画面更真实。苹果搭配了十多个高清摄像头、激光雷达等传感器获取周围的环境，自研两款芯片处理这些图像；定制 4K 分辨率、每秒刷新 120 次的 micro OLED 屏幕显示图像，再经过优化的三层镜片折射，让图像更逼真、通透，最终传递到人眼的视网膜上。VR 行业常用每 1° 视野中像素点（角分辨率，PPD）综合评判头戴设备的显示效果，达到人眼的效果需要到 60。现在的设备普遍只有 20 左右，而 Vision Pro 做到了 40。\\n\\n 让操作更简单。现在的头戴设备几乎都要用控制器操控，苹果认为这是 “恼人的工具”，收购多家面部追踪公司，用多个传感器实时追踪人眼和手势——视线就是鼠标、两指一掐就是点击。\\n 让近视眼有更好的体验。现在近视用户使用头戴设备，要么戴着眼镜把脑袋挤进去，要么贴上近视镜片。苹果是为数不多在发布会上介绍近视用户怎么用设备的公司，它与蔡司合作定制了适合 Vision Pro 的近视镜片，吸附到设备上，可以保证完美的体验。\\n\\n一位参与 Vision Pro 研发的前苹果制造工程师告诉《晚点 LatePost》，对于工业设计师确定的参数，负责制造团队基本没有任何发言权，必须想尽一切办法去实现。\\n\\n具体到近视镜片的硬件模组上，苹果会与供应商一起制定切割镜片的方案，尽可能提前想到用户可能会遇到的极端情况，比如确保磁吸模块能适应不同度数（厚度）的镜片，每个细节都会经过数百上千次的调试，扩大视力矫正范围的同时，不影响显示屏性能或视线追踪的准确性。 [...] 库克常戴不足 30 克重的 MYKITA 眼镜。今天的技术不足以造出这样轻便、高画质的 AR 设备。罗克韦尔的解决办法是，以 VR（虚拟现实）的方式实现 AR（增强现实）：\\n\\n戴上 Vision Pro，用户眼前依然是两块屏幕，看不到外面。但 12 个摄像头、激光雷达和红外传感器捕捉外部画面，实时渲染出实景一般的图像呈现在屏幕上，让人有看穿屏幕的错觉。旋转 Vision Pro 右上方的旋钮，就能从以假乱真的外部世界（AR）切换到沉浸的虚拟空间（VR），比如坐在丛林里看恐怖片。\\n\\n与此同时，苹果还在设备外部加了一块的弧形屏幕，用来显示传感器收集到的用户眼部画面，做出透视的效果。苹果将其称为 EyeSight。\\n\\nVision Pro 内外布满摄像头等传感器。上方是 Vision Pro 外部情况，有 8 个高清摄像头、2 个景深相机、1 个激光雷达。下方是 Vision Pro 内部情况，有 4 个红外摄像头和一圈 LED。图片来自苹果。\\n\\nVision Pro 会在外置屏幕上模拟用户眼部画面。图片来自苹果。\\n\\n为了在 VR 设备上做出一款 AR 眼镜，苹果连续收购了十几家有相关人才和技术的创业公司，自行开发了新处理器、光学镜片模组、操作系统、应用开发平台等关键组件。到研发后期，苹果每年都在这个项目上投入 10 亿美元。\\n\\n堪比 SpaceX 造火箭的投入，只为了解决一些特别基础的需求： [...] 散热较差是苹果将高算力芯片塞进头显中带来的直接问题。直到 2022 年，罗克韦尔与苹果董事会成员展示成品时，散热问题也没有解决，不得不延期发布产品。在发布会上，苹果展现出来的最终解决方案是加上两个风扇帮助散热。\\n\\n前述苹果 Vision Pro 团队前员工告诉《晚点 LatePost》，他感受最深的是苹果对设备细节的关注。2021 年底，一个硬件模组到了量产前最后一个步骤，需要评估最终的质量。\\n\\n苹果测试它从一米、两米、五米的高度掉下来后情况怎样。最后发现，设备从五米处掉落后，包裹镜片的塑料框有万分之一、二的概率会裂开。\\n\\n“从副总裁到基层，整条线上的所有人都介入了，重新设计方案，供应商也重新调整。” 他说。临近产品发布，苹果和供应商的工程师们加班、熬夜去解决这个问题。\\n\\n一个没有工厂的企业，一年花 100 亿美元买设备推动制造技术\\n\\n乔布斯时期，苹果可以很低成本找到关键技术并突破。2003 年，苹果一个 6 人交互设计团队做了一个概念设备，两根手指在屏幕上点点画画，就能拉动网页、放大图片。这就是后来的多点触控，今天每个人在手机上的操控界面。\\n\\n当时苹果刚走出 2000 年纳斯达克崩盘的谷底，工程师们多年不换电脑，多点触控技术在 Windows PC 上完成。但乔布斯组织起 200 多人团队，逼着他们把触控的电脑先做到 iPad 的尺寸，再做到了 3.5 英寸屏幕上，成为 iPhone，彻底改变了我们世界的运作方式，为一代互联网公司搭起创业基础设施。\\n\\n微软研究院的工程师差不多在同期给董事长比尔·盖茨（Bill Gates）演示了多点触控技术。最后在 iPhone 发售前一个月，微软发布了一台桌子大小的触控电脑——Surface Desk。\\n\\n微软 2007 年发布的 Surface，运行一个定制版的 Windows Vista 操作系统。\",\n        \"score\": 0.7606688,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.ednchina.com/news/a13012.html\",\n        \"title\": \"拆解Vision Pro（一）：发现一个非常奇怪的设计\",\n        \"content\": \"Q5eednc\\n\\n当您第一次戴上Vision Pro 时，它本身会自动进行瞳距调整，并通过电机调整镜片的位置。Q5eednc\\n\\n苹果商店有一台机器，可以在您参加演示时确定近似处方眼镜的强度。对于患有可能会干扰眼球追踪的眼部疾病（如斜视）的用户，Vision Pro在辅助功能中提供了替代交互控制。然而，我们听说有散光的人（占人口的 40%）不适合佩戴镜片。Q5eednc\\n\\n处方镜片本身需要与耳机“配对”。这一决定已经带来了糟糕的用户界面，约翰·格鲁伯（John Gruber）在他的审查单元中收到了错误的校准代码，导致眼动追踪表现不佳。原则上我们讨厌零件配对，并且必须有一种方法可以在允许使用第三方镜头的同时进行校准。Q5eednc\\n\\n### R1和M2芯片\\n\\n该耳机在 M2 Mac 芯片上运行，与新的 R1 芯片配合使用，后者专门负责处理来自 12 个摄像头、LiDAR 传感器和 TrueDepth 摄像头的输入，所有这些都具有最小的延迟。使用 AR，您需要尽快将现实世界的摄像头视图投射到用户的眼睛中，否则他们感知到的动作将与他们所看到的不匹配，这就是一张通往 Vomitsville 的快速门票。 Q5eednc\\n\\n为了跟上，R1使用实时操作系统。这意味着任务总是在固定的时间内执行。我们的大多数计算机都运行在分时操作系统上，该操作系统会动态安排任务，并可能导致速度变慢。想想紧张的鼠标光标或旋转的沙滩球，您就明白了。这对于像直通视频和对象渲染这样重要的东西来说是行不通的。那里的任何故障都会像黑客帝国中的故障一样，往好里说会令人不舒服，往坏里说则完全令人作呕。它甚至可能导致您绊倒和跌倒。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n### 一个非常奇怪的设计 [...] Q5eednc\\n\\n### 一个非常奇怪的设计\\n\\n最初的 iPhone 也做了类似的事情。当其动力不足的芯片无法跟上渲染快速滚动的页面时，它会切换到灰白棋盘格，以跟上您所有的轻弹和滑动操作。苹果将响应能力置于图形保真度之上。这一次，他们优先考虑了图形保真度和响应能力，并在电池寿命、重量和热量方面受到了影响。考虑到这种体验对苹果 AR 体验的重要性，这可能是第一代设备的正确选择。Q5eednc\\n\\nVision Pro很重，玻璃很脆弱，而且系绳电池可能会很烦人。但苹果已经成功地将 Mac 的强大功能以及新型专用 AR 芯片的性能整合到一台可以戴在脸上的电脑中。Q5eednc\\n\\n苹果公司在 EyeSight 屏幕上显然花了很多年的时间才创造出来，但它分辨率低，并且给耳机中对重量最敏感的部分增加了大量的体积、重量、复杂性和费用。Q5eednc\\n\\n我们的分析还没有完成：这个设备内部还有很多东西需要研究。下一次，我们将深入研究内部显示器、传感器阵列，并给予可修复性评分。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n 报名IIC Shanghai 2026（3.31-4.1 上海浦东丽思卡尔顿酒店），掌握全球芯动向，领取丰厚福利>>  \\n  \\n2026国际集成电路展览会暨研讨会，聚焦AI 芯片、汽车电子、工业控制、通信系统、绿色能源等关键应用场景，汇聚全球IC 设计、EDA 工具、IP 授权、先进封装等领域的顶尖企业与专家，通过「2 大主题峰会+ 权威奖项评选+ 垂直技术论坛+ 展览展示」四大核心板块，打造贯通芯片设计制造、能源技术革新、产品商业化落地的超级产业连接器。\\n\\n责编：Demi\\n\\n阅读全文，请先 登录 [...] 前置护目镜是 Vision Pro 的标志性特征，现在评论纷至沓来，这也是最具争议性的特征之一。Q5eednc\\n\\nEyeSight 的专利描述了三种显示模式：“内部聚焦”、“外部参与”和“请勿打扰”。该专利有一页又一页的图像可以显示在屏幕上——各种卡通动物的眼睛、其他传感器捕获的生物特征分析、用户与亲人交谈时的心形。内部摄像头可以读取情绪状态并根据这些情绪状态投射图像。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n很酷的想法。实际上，EyeSight 显示屏非常昏暗且分辨率低，评论家表示很难在上面看到太多内容。《华尔街日报》的乔安娜·斯特恩 (Joanna Stern)称其“很难看见”，而马克斯·布朗利 (又名 MKBHD) 则表示，“当我戴着耳机时，你几乎看不到我的眼睛。” Q5eednc\\n\\n事实证明，当 EyeSight 显示你的眼睛时，它不仅仅是显示你眼睛的单个视频；它还显示你的眼睛。它正在显示一堆你眼睛的视频。通过探索玻璃外壳内部，我们发现了前置显示屏的三层：加宽层、透镜层和 OLED 显示屏本身。Q5eednc\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\n### 为什么视觉看起来如此不稳定？\\n\\nQ5eednc\\n\\nApple 希望实现一些非常具体的目标：带有眼睛的动画 3D 面孔。为了实现这一目标，他们必须做出非常战略性的设计选择和妥协。Q5eednc\\n\\n人类的大脑对面孔和表情非常敏感，这就是恐怖谷之所以存在的原因，其中一部分就是深度感知。Apple 需要创造可信的 3D 效果。3D 渲染看起来不像真正的 3D 的原因之一是它们缺乏立体效果。为了让某些东西看起来像 3D，我们需要用每只眼睛看到略有不同的图像。Vision Pro 通过双凸透镜解决了这个问题。Q5eednc\",\n        \"score\": 0.6682966,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.realwear.com.cn/news/2306apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro重新定义“远程办公” 给工业端带来无限畅想\",\n        \"content\": \"所以，面对一线作业人员，或者一线使用者来说，衡量一款软件的好坏要从三个维度出发进行判别：\\n\\n\\\"第一，要有非常好的使用体验，毕竟这是一款高度体验的产品。甚至，对于这种软件的体验要求比手机要高的多。一个设备戴在头上，如何跟它进行交互——什么时候用手势，什么时候用眼神，什么时候用语音，这种要求远远高于对手机的要求。针对这一点来讲，不光在硬件上有好的体验，在内容的设计上也要结合硬件提供与之匹配的优秀体验。内容层面，是通过语音交互，还是姿态交互，亦或者根据使用场景自动切换，这些因素都至关重要。所以，关乎软件应用是否足够优秀，它的体验感非常重要。第二，在工业领域或者企业应用领域，要求的不是发散，不是创造性，是收敛，是精准。我们给一线人员提供的，或者给企业管理者提供的数据和应用的结论必须是非常准确的，我们必须要直击一线使用者的痛点，解决他的问题，搜集到正确数据，做出正确的AI判断……所以，它是一个收敛的过程，不是一个发散的过程。这是判断软件应用好的第二个标准，它一定是精准的，不是开放式的，发散式的。第三，我们认为一个好的软件应用，或者工业企业的数字内容，它是一个系统。我们所提供的解决方案所为企业提供的价值，不是单单针对戴设备的人，或者使用者。它是整个工业互联网，或者工业元宇宙世界中的一个终端。除此之外，还有其他的终端、其他的角色。这个角色不一定佩戴设备，他可能是数据分析师，或者企业的决策者。所以，好的数据内容需要一个系统的架构。如果是一个有缺陷的解决方案，可能只是满足了某一个角色在这个系统中的应用，这不是一个好的方案，没有系统性，没有完整度。\\\" [...] # 新闻资讯\\n\\n新闻资讯\\n\\n2023-06-14\\n\\n# Apple Vision Pro重新定义“远程办公” 给工业端带来无限畅想\\n\\n所有XR行业从业者都等这一刻等得太久了。\\n\\n终于，苹果在今年的WWDC发布了已经连续“跳票”数次发布会的MR眼镜Apple Vision Pro。而这款产品也真的没有让行业内外所有关注的人失望，无论是从产品的工业设计、交互体验、系统操作等各个维度，这都是一款足以让世人惊艳的产品。\\n\\n6.14apple2\\n\\nApple Vision Pro远程办公场景图\\n\\n尽管这是一款主要面向C端用户的产品，但是其中也有部分功能让大家看到了Apple Vision Pro在远程办公方面的应用。当类似于“王牌特工”中的场景真正出现在现实生活中的时候，也让大家看到了Apple Vision Pro未来在B端应用的潜在方向。\\n\\n瑞欧威尔联合创始人兼CEO李波博士，就对于Apple Vision Pro这款产品的问世，以深耕XR行业多年的亲历者角度，表达了其对于这款产品的一些不同维度的观点和看法。\\n\\n“苹果的MR眼镜已经进入到空间计算的水准，是MR眼镜中天花板级的产品。”\\n\\n在李波博士看来，苹果MR眼镜的问世，一定会带动整个行业的发展，这其中有几个维度：\\n\\n第一是对于相关供应链的推进。基于苹果的体量以及苹果对于产品质量的要求，一定会推进很多供应商支持这个项目，也就意味着未来这些供应商的资源可能也会推进关联行业的整体发展。就像我们走过的智能手机时代一样，iPhone把手机产业相关供应链能力带起来之后，所有关联行业都受益了。 [...] 足够优秀的硬件匹配足以支撑起完美用户体验的内容生态，苹果的MR眼镜的问世已经让每一位身处这个行业从业者兴奋不已，相信这会激发一场“蝴蝶效应”，推动整个XR产业的正向发展，无论是硬件产品，亦或是软件生态；无论是面对消费市场，亦或是面对企业市场。\\n\\n上一篇 强强联合！瑞欧威尔与TeamViewer全球战略合作，赋能工业一线\\n\\n下一篇 瑞欧威尔吸睛亮相“苏州智博会”工业AR+AI点燃数字革命\\n\\n电话咨询 400-8520-729\\n\\n本站使用Cookies技术用于必要的功能和分析，以便提升您的浏览体验。\\n\\n| 名称 | 域名 | 用途 | 时长 | 安全 |\\n ---  --- \\n| contact-collected | .realwear.com.cn | 下载资料 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| csrftoken | .realwear.com.cn | 数据校验 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| email-collected | .realwear.com.cn | 下载资料 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| sessionid | .realwear.com.cn | 保持会话 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| wtm | .realwear.com.cn | 隐私设置 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n| wtm\\\\_id | .realwear.com.cn | 隐私设置 | 365天 | HTTPS |\\n\\n#### 请输入您的联系方式\",\n        \"score\": 0.63804686,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro spatial design industrial applications\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://7t.ai/blog/apple-vision-pro-uses-for-business-spatial-video-for-any-industry/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro Uses for Business - Spatial Video for Any Industry\",\n        \"content\": \"Apple Vision Pro uses abound, the applications for this technology are expected to grow by leaps and bounds thanks to one key capability: you can capture spatial video for these VR goggles using an iPhone 15 Pro! This is a significant change from what was long the status quo: you had to hire a professional film crew to capture 3D or spatial video for use in conjunction with virtual reality headsets. And this was, as one might expect, very costly and time-consuming. In many cases, it was cost prohibitive.\\n\\nBut Apple Vision Pro and its ability to utilize footage captured on a iPhone 15 Pro means that organizations of all sizes, in all industries, with all budget sizes can now utilize virtual reality technology, making Apple Vision Pro a key component of an extended reality (XR) strategy. [...] Spatial video can be combined with artificial intelligence to generate a truly one-of-a-kind experience that allows the viewer to interact with the virtual environment. As with VR product showcases, this Apple Vision Pro use case for high-end service offerings brings optimal results when paired with an on-site virtual reality lounge, where prospective customers can experience virtual reality right there at a company’s premises.\\n\\nThis Apple Vision Pro use case is ideal for high-end service offerings, such as travel and destination marketing, vehicle customization services or the creation of bespoke designer goods. [...] Apple Vision Pro virtual reality goggles use spatial video technology — sometimes called immersive video — which creates a dynamic, three-dimensional environment for the user. This actually represents an improvement over traditional 3D video, which allows you to view a scene from a static position. If you move, the scene may become distorted. But spatial video features 6DOF (six degrees of freedom), allowing the user to move around within the environment and the surrounding digital environment shifts as your perspective shifts. This shift in perspective is the key difference between spatial video vs 3D video footage.\",\n        \"score\": 0.843393,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://eleks.com/blog/apples-vision-pro-revolutionising-industries-through-spatial-computing/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple's Vision Pro: Revolutionising Industries Through Spatial ...\",\n        \"content\": \"While it's impossible to predict the future with certainty, the advancements made in VR technology and the versatility of applications across industries make a compelling case. The potential benefits in healthcare, education, entertainment, design, and collaboration are significant.\\n\\nAs the technology continues to evolve and become more accessible, it has the potential to reshape how we interact with digital content in our daily lives.\\n\\nEmbracing the Future of Work\\n\\nApple's Vision Pro is set to redefine spatial computing and unleash its transformative potential across industries. By seamlessly blending the digital and physical worlds, this device opens up new horizons in healthcare innovations, education, and beyond. [...] Apple's Vision Pro: Revolutionising Industries Through Spatial Computing| ELEKS: Enterprise Software Development, Technology Consulting\\n\\nSkip to main content\\n\\n headsets, it showcases advanced VR capabilities that can transform various sectors.\\n\\nIn the words of the tech giant, welcome to the era of spatial computing, where Apple's Vision Pro is set to revolutionise industries such as healthcare and education.\\n\\nWhat We Know About Apple's Vision Pro\\n\\nApple Vision Prorepresents a leap forward in spatial computing, seamlessly merging digital content with the physical world. The device introduces innovative methods of interaction, utilising eye, hand, and voice commands to navigate effortlessly. [...] Vision Pro redefines how users engage with their favourite applications with an infinite canvas and the ability to scale and arrange apps anywhere. It offers a truly immersive theatre experience, brings memories to life through 3D photos and videos, facilitates meaningful collaborations, and showcases Apple's meticulous design expertise.\\n\\nImage 128: Apple's Vision Goggles in Technology Niche\\n\\nPotential Applications of VR Across Industries\\n\\n### Healthcare Innovation\\n\\nWith Apple's Vision Pro, healthcare professionals and researchers can leverage VR technology for a wide range of applications. For example, surgeons can use virtual simulations to practise complex procedures, improving their skills and reducing the risk of errors during actual surgeries.\",\n        \"score\": 0.83093774,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.persistent.com/blogs/spatial-design-designing-with-dimension-for-apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Spatial Design – Designing with Dimension for Apple Vision Pro\",\n        \"content\": \"We leverage all the available XR platforms, tools and packages to create XR experiences for different use cases across industry sectors like Healthcare, Manufacturing, Retail, Telecommunication, etc.\\n\\n      Our XR solutions cater to different challenges faced in these industries for various use cases:\\n\\n      + Operations and troubleshooting processes\\n      + Complex production processes\\n      + Field support\\n      + Different product experiences along with guidance\\n\\n      By harnessing these XR technologies, Persistent helps businesses deliver outstanding experiences which –\\n\\n      + Improve efficiency\\n      + Improve productivity\\n      + Reduce costs\\n      + Provide enhanced intuitive user interactions [...] (Image Credit Apple)\\n\\n      In our previous article, we talked about how spatial computing plays a significant role in building the Extended Reality (XR) experiences. In this article, we will talk about Apple Vision Pro – Apple’s Spatial computer and the transformative power of Apple’s visionOS in shaping the future of spatial design.\\n\\n      ###### Apple Vision Pro\\n\\n      \\n\\n      Fig 1. Apple Vision Pro headset (Image Credit Apple)\\n\\n      Launched on June 5th, 2023, Apple Vision Pro enables the blending of digital data and physical world surrounding the users, providing an interactive and immersive experience and allows users to experience Augmented Reality (AR), Mixed Reality (MR) and Virtual Reality (VR) applications. [...] Cloud & InfrastructureBusiness ApplicationsModernization & Digital TransformationIntelligent AutomationData & AnalyticsCX TransformationEnterprise Applications & IntegrationsEnterprise IT SecurityInternet of Things (IoT) About\\n\\n          Corporate ValuesLeadership TeamInvestorsEventsIn the NewsPress ReleasesAwards and RecognitionsEnvironmental, Social and GovernancePersistent FoundationDiversity and InclusionInnovation LabSheShapesAIPersistent AlumniLocationsContact Us Careers\\n           Contact Us\\n\\n      # Spatial Design – Designing with Dimension for Apple Vision Pro\\n\\n      Blog by Shilpa Ramteke, posted on November 3, 2023 in Persistent.AI\\n\\n       \\n\\n      (Image Credit Apple)\",\n        \"score\": 0.829285,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.infosys.com/services/incubating-emerging-technologies/documents/apple-vision.pdf\",\n        \"title\": \"[PDF] Apple Vision Pro and spatial computer - what it mean for enterprise ...\",\n        \"content\": \"Besides media and entertainment companies, industries poised to benefit significantly from Apple Vision Pro include: Healthcare, with applications in medical training and remote patient care Manufacturing, by enhancing processes and training through augmented reality Retail, through virtual try-on experiences and interactive displays Marketing, with immersive campaigns and product visualizations Education, by transforming learning experiences with virtual content Travel, ofering virtual exploration and augmented reality guides to enhance the tourism sector External Document © 2024 Infosys Limited External Document © 2024 Infosys Limited What Infosys is Doing in this Space Infosys set up an extended reality (XR) practice almost a decade back, which helps its clients discover meaningful use [...] VIEW POINT APPLE VISION PRO AND SPATIAL COMPUTING - WHAT IT MEANS FOR ENTERPRISES Abstract Apple Vision Pro’s launch on Feb’24 once again has brought excitement to the future of immersive experiences. At WWDC 2023, rather than pitching a futuristic, sci-fi, “Ready Player One” Metaverse type of experience, Tim Cook introduced it as Apple’s first spatial computer which instead looks at virtualizing the many screens we already encounter on a day-to-day basis (websites, movies, notes, messages, FaceTime), in an innovative and immersive way. In this article, we present our views on the recently launched Apple Vision Pro and what it means for enterprise applications, based on our prior experience and the knowledge that we have gathered by trying out the goggles first-hand. [...] Apple Current Focus and Eventual Adoption at Enterprises Apple is bringing spatial computing to the consideration of the masses in a way that makes complex technology feel approachable, simple to use, and familiar. Apple has initially positioned it for consumers, with mostly personal use cases being shown during the launch. However, Vision Pro is equally useful for designers, developers, enterprise and industry professionals. Promotional videos were also largely centered around people wearing the Vision Pro in their homes, promising something akin to playing on a big screen TV rather than a bespoke XR solution. Although the price point of $3500 is still way out of reach for most, it brings consumer adoption one step closer through better immersive experiences. Expectations are that it\",\n        \"score\": 0.77487355,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/04/apple-vision-pro-brings-a-new-era-of-spatial-computing-to-business/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro brings a new era of spatial computing to business\",\n        \"content\": \"Apple offers developers a variety of resources, including powerful APIs, rich documentation, global developer labs, Develop in Swift Tutorials, and the visionOS simulator to help companies bring game-changing Apple Vision Pro experiences to life. To further support developers, today Apple is announcing the Enterprise Spatial Design Lab, providing hands-on support from Apple to help enterprises bring apps from concept to reality. The immersive sessions will be available beginning this summer at developer.apple.com. In addition, Deloitte announced today it is expanding its Apple practice to include a new Academy for Apple Vision Pro. The practice includes more than 100 practitioners trained to deliver visionOS solutions to clients, with a series of one-week, instructor-led courses to help [...] PTC’s Onshape Vision apptransforms the way product designers and engineers view, interact with, and collaborate on complex 3D models.\\n\\nGuided Work\\n\\nGuided work requires the context of a person’s surroundings, such as a utility service technician who needs access to work orders or schematics.Resolvehas reimagined how building engineers can plan for and access information they need to make decisions about systems behind walls, including HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and fire sprinkler lines. Rather than use static paper plans, users can review high-detail plans and 3D models on Apple Vision Pro, enabling architects, builders, and maintenance workers to see, fix, and comment, enhancing the entire life cycle of a construction project. [...] PTC’s Onshape Vision apptransforms the way product designers and engineers view, interact with, and collaborate on complex 3D models.\\n\\nGuided Work\\n\\nGuided work requires the context of a person’s surroundings, such as a utility service technician who needs access to work orders or schematics.Resolvehas reimagined how building engineers can plan for and access information they need to make decisions about systems behind walls, including HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and fire sprinkler lines. Rather than use static paper plans, users can review high-detail plans and 3D models on Apple Vision Pro, enabling architects, builders, and maintenance workers to see, fix, and comment, enhancing the entire life cycle of a construction project.\",\n        \"score\": 0.76512027,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Apple Vision Pro manufacturing automotive design\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://kodytechnolab.com/blog/vision-pro-for-automotive-industry/\",\n        \"title\": \"Vision Pro for Automotive Industry: Transforming Design & ...\",\n        \"content\": \"Here is how it benefits your design process:\\n\\nUsing VisionOS in your automotive design improves innovation speed, lowers costs, and enhances product quality. Staying updated with the latest Apple Vision Pro trends ensures your business maintains a clear advantage in the market.\\n\\n## Vision Pro Use Cases in Automotive Training: Smarter, Faster, Safer\\n\\nTraining is essential to maintaining safety and quality in the automotive industry. Vision Pro technology transforms training by making it more immersive, efficient, and safe. Here’s how Vision Pro enhances key training areas:\\n\\n### Virtual Reality Driver Training for Customers [...] The automotive industry is at a pivotal moment. Vision Pro for automotive industry offers unprecedented opportunities to innovate across design, sales, training, and maintenance. If you want to stay competitive, reduce costs, and accelerate your time-to-market, embracing Vision Pro technology is no longer optional, it’s essential.\\n\\nKody Technolab, a leading VisionOS App Development Company, specializes in creating tailored, secure, and scalable Vision Pro applications for automotive businesses. Our expert team helps you navigate challenges, ensuring seamless integration and delivering solutions that maximize your ROI. [...] In summary, Vision Pro for the automotive industry drives productivity, lowers costs, and accelerates innovation across design, sales, and training. This technology supports your core business functions and helps you maintain a competitive edge in today’s automotive market.\\n\\nIf you’re looking to hire expert developers for your VisionOS projects, be sure to read our comprehensive guide, How to Hire VisionOS App Developers.\\n\\n## Redefining Automotive Design with Vision Pro for Automotive Industry\\n\\nVisionOS is revolutionizing how you design vehicles by streamlining the entire process from concept modeling to virtual validation, enabling faster, more precise, and collaborative workflows.\\n\\nadvanced automotive vr experience\\n\\nHere is how it benefits your design process:\",\n        \"score\": 0.80442166,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://manufacturingdigital.com/articles/porsche-ag-mhp-virtual-training-uses-apple-vision-pro\",\n        \"title\": \"Porsche AG & MHP Virtual Training Uses Apple Vision Pro\",\n        \"content\": \"Article\\n\\nSmart Manufacturing\\n\\n# Porsche AG & MHP Virtual Training Uses Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nByRachael Brown\\n\\nMay 17, 2024\\n\\nundefined mins\\n\\nShare\\n\\nShare\\n\\nMarkus Wambach, COO and Member of the Management Board at MHP\\n\\nMHP and Porsche AG have been using 3D training to upskill production line staff, addressing the digital skills gap in supply chain manufacturing\\n\\nLeading automotive manufacturer Porsche has partnered with management and IT consultancy MHP to deliver innovative augmented reality training solutions.\\n\\nOn 2 February, 2024, the Apple Vision Pro was released, with major commercial and industry applications. Like Epson’s smart glasses, the futuristic headset can be utilised to bring interactivity and realism to employee training exercises without real-world costs or risks. [...] The long-term goal of both companies is to formally implement the Apple Vision Pro as a means to train and educate employees for production. The solution has the potential to revolutionise other areas, including after-sales in the automotive industry.\\n\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\nMake sure you check out the latest edition of Manufacturing Digital and also sign up to our global conference series - Procurement & Supply Chain 2024 & Sustainability LIVE 2024  \\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\  \\nManufacturing Digital is a BizClik brand.\\n\\n## Company portals\\n\\n \\n\\n  ### MHP – A Porsche Company\\n \\n\\n  ### Porsche\\n\\n## Tags\\n\\nApplePorsche AGMHPtrainingaugmented reality [...] To demonstrate the effectiveness of the Apple Vision Pro, a showcase event was held in partnership with Porsche at its Zuffenhausen plant in Germany. Part of the plant's production process was completed using the headsets' realistic 3D training, and CAD data of a welding rotary table and manufacturing robot was realistically mapped in a “shop floor training” session.\\n\\nThe employee saw the entire task laid out, step by step, inside the headset alongside repair instructions superimposed on a 3D model. This process increased employee satisfaction and reduced errors, with options for assessment and certification.\\n\\nWhat users see whilst training in the Apple Vision Pro\",\n        \"score\": 0.7395922,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/alexlevin/2025/04/24/porsches-new-apple-vision-pro-app-lets-you-design-your-dream-911/\",\n        \"title\": \"Porsche's New Apple Vision Pro App Lets You Design Your Dream ...\",\n        \"content\": \"More broadly, as luxury brands across various sectors – including fashion houses like Gucci, luggage makers such as Rimowa, jewelers like Bulgari, and automotive manufacturers – experiment with the Apple Vision Pro, spatial computing and XR devices as customer touchpoints, legitimate questions arise concerning the genuine value proposition versus the potential for expensive novelties. [...] Ultimately, while questions of immediate utility versus novelty arise in the context of consumer-facing automotive applications of spatial computing, it’s important to acknowledge that this technology has already proven its value as a significant tool in the design world. Across architecture, interior design, and for global design teams collaborating on product development, spatial computing offers tangible benefits in visualization, collaboration, and efficiency. This established utility in the design and creation process provides a crucial context as automotive brands explore its potential as a new customer touchpoint.\\n\\nAn Impending Spatial Computing Race [...] Porsche's New Apple Vision Pro App Lets You Design Your Dream 911\\n\\n\\n\\ndpa/picture alliance via Getty Images\\n\\nPorsche has launched its \\\"911 Spirit 70\\\" app for Apple Vision Pro, marking the luxury automaker’s first significant foray into customer-facing spatial computing. The new application, available today on the Vision Pro App Store, allows users to place a virtual Porsche 911 in their physical environment, examine it from all angles, and customize it in real-time.\\n\\nImage 2: Screen capture from the \\\"911 Spirit 70\\\" app for Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nScreen capture from the \\\"911 Spirit 70\\\" app for Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nDr. Ing. h.c. F. Porsche AG\",\n        \"score\": 0.73778254,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro for Business\",\n        \"content\": \"# The future of business starts with vision.\\n\\nSpatial Analogue shown in video\\n\\nCAE mobile immersive training shown in video\\n\\nVisage Ease VP\\\\ shown in video\\n\\nPorsche Car Configurator shown in video\\n\\nApple Vision Pro reinvents what’s possible for business, opening up completely new ways to work. Teams can collaborate in spatial workspaces, streamline workflows, train efficiently, and create incredible customer experiences. From manufacturing to healthcare and beyond, spatial computing with Apple Vision Pro can transform entire industries.\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Redesign the design process.\\n\\n3DLive\\\\\\n\\n### Speed through reviews. [...] ### Demos shoppers can see — and feel.\\n\\nDeliver immersive product demos that help shoppers configure, try, and buy products like never before. At Porsche, customers personalize their dream cars in life size with Apple Vision Pro and experience them in a vivid, delightful way.\\n\\nA customer in a Porsche showroom wearing Apple Vision Pro views a 3D projection of a sportscar and talks with an employee\\nA customer in a Porsche showroom wearing Apple Vision Pro views a 3D projection of a sportscar and talks with an employee\\n\\n### Elevating customer exploration.\\n\\nBuild engaging experiences like augmented interior designs, virtual product try-ons, and visuals placed in real-life environments. And with the JigSpace app, manufacturing leaders like EVAPCO can transform customer education.\",\n        \"score\": 0.72042775,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"http://www.designlife-cycle.com/apple-vision-pro\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro - Design Life-Cycle\",\n        \"content\": \"The production of AR lenses for the Apple Vision Pro begins with the extraction of raw materials. The primary materials include silica, silicon, and various rare earth elements, which are essential for manufacturing microchips and other electronic components. The extraction process itself is resource-intensive, requiring substantial amounts of water and energy. For instance, silicon, a key component, is derived from silica found in sand. The refining process of silicon is energy-intensive, involving high-temperature furnaces that consume large amounts of electricity, predominantly sourced from fossil fuels . During manufacturing, the production of microchips for AR lenses generates significant waste and emissions. Mining of these materials is energy-intensive and leads to significant [...] The Apple Vision Pro is a brand new spatial computing device released by Apple in 2024. This device is worn as a headset and weaves reality with a digital landscape to create a unique user experience. The Vision Pro captures reality through its many cameras and displays it to the user through screens. This report aims to detail the life cycle of these components. The life cycle of the Apple Vision Pro's cameras involve the acquisition and processing of raw materials. The introduction of raw materials is most heavily involved in their acquisition and processing steps, but some new materials must also be introduced in distribution, maintenance, recycling, and waste. All of the materials used at every step will be accounted for in this life cycle analysis.\",\n        \"score\": 0.70799106,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"query\": \"Vision Pro CAD 3D modeling industrial use\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.onshape.com/en/blog/apple-vision-pro-cad-app-use-cases\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro and Product Design: 4 Practical Use Cases\",\n        \"content\": \"### INDUSTRY SOLUTIONS\\n\\nEliminate inefficiencies of traditional product development, no matter what industry. From concept to production, teams using Onshape gain the agility and control they need to innovate without compromise.\\n\\n### Aerospace & Defense\\n\\n### Automotive\\n\\n### Consumer Products\\n\\n### Education\\n\\n### Electronics\\n\\n### Energy\\n\\n### Government\\n\\n### Machine Design\\n\\n### Medical Devices\\n\\n### Robotics\\n\\n### Startups\\n\\nSign In Arrow\\n\\nDownload the Onshape Mobile App\\n\\nBlog Hero Image\\n\\n# Apple Vision Pro and Product Design: 4 Practical Use Cases\\n\\nauthor image\\n\\nThe integration of the Onshape Vision app with Apple Vision Pro represents a significant leap forward in spatial computing, offering engineers and designers a more intuitive and interactive way to visualize and manipulate 3D models. [...] Here’s a closer look at how this technology can transform your design and review processes.\\n\\n## Onshape Vision: Bridging the Gap Between Digital and Physical\\n\\nOnshape Vision leverages the spatial computing capabilities of Apple Vision Pro to bring a new level of immersion to 3D CAD models.\\n\\nThe app bridges Onshape’s CAD & PDM mobile platform running on an Apple iPad or iPhone with Apple Vision Pro’s headset, empowering users to interact with parts and assemblies in a way that's both intuitive and realistic.\\n\\nImagine scaling an assembly to fit on your desk, grabbing components with your hands, rotating them, and inspecting them from any angle. This is spatial computing in action: enhancing the review and inspection of digital designs by situating them within the physical world. [...] Example: Service technicians use Onshape Vision to interact with a 3D model of bespoke heavy equipment in a training session. This immersive experience allows them to familiarize themselves with the customer's specific model, discussing and practicing maintenance procedures in a virtual environment that mimics actual conditions.\\n\\n### Exploring Customization and Personalization Options\\n\\nBenefit: Offers customers a unique, interactive experience to explore and visualize customization options, leading to increased satisfaction and confidence in their purchase decisions.\",\n        \"score\": 0.7752821,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.apple.com/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Apple Vision Pro for Business\",\n        \"content\": \"### Train teams smarter, wherever they are.\\n\\nProvide immersive, true-to-life training on key equipment anytime, anywhere. Industry leaders like CAE use Apple Vision Pro to train pilots in detailed simulations, leading to better retention for full-scale simulator sessions.1\\n\\nA person's hand ajusts a control knob in a 3D projection of a plane's cockpit\\nA person's hand ajusts a control knob in a 3D projection of a plane's cockpit\\n\\n### Bring a new perspective to learning.\\n\\nEasily instruct and simplify learning with lifelike 3D experiences. Apps like Complete HeartX help medical students explore anatomy in stunning detail using photorealistic models, videos, and simulations. [...] ### Get on the same page, product, or prototype.\\n\\nProduct designers can easily collaborate and review CAD models together with onsite and remote teams. Using PTC’s Onshape Vision app, stakeholders get real-time access to models and components in an immersive workspace.\\n\\nA 3D projection of a CAD model of machinery and information about the machinery, projected into an office room\\nA 3D projection of a CAD model of machinery and information about the machinery, projected into an office room\\n\\n## Immersive Training\\n\\n### Simulated training. Real results.\\n\\nBILT 3D Immersive Instructions\\\\\\n\\n### Train teams smarter, wherever they are. [...] A 3D projection of an EVAPCO Cooling Tower in an industrial space, with controls to flip through information about the tower\\nA 3D projection of an EVAPCO Cooling Tower in an industrial space, with controls to flip through information about the tower\\n\\n### Showcase products without the setup.\\n\\nCustomers can see, explore, and step inside products virtually. Decathlon’s custom app lets shoppers interact with true-to-scale outdoor equipment without opening a box.\\n\\nA 3D projection of a camping tent overlaid in a sporting goods showroom, and a floating window shows additional product information\\nA 3D projection of a camping tent overlaid in a sporting goods showroom, and a floating window shows additional product information\\n\\n## Productivity\\n\\n### Infinite workspace. Ultimate workflow.\",\n        \"score\": 0.74004334,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.shapr3d.com/products/vision-os\",\n        \"title\": \"CAD on Vision Pro | Meet Shapr3D Spatial CAD\",\n        \"content\": \"iPadOS\\n\\n or later\\n\\nInstallation guide\\n\\nContact sales\\n\\nA few details now.  \\nA tailored solution next.\\n\\n# Shapr3D for apple vision pro\\n\\nNow enable real-time 3D design and editing directly on the Vision Pro, equipping your team with precise 3D communication and collaboration in the immersive environment of Spatial Computer-Aided Design.\\n\\nStart modelingSign upRequest a demo\\n\\n## See how enterprises collaborate on the only CAD to run natively on Apple Vision Pro.\\n\\n## Reduce Reliance on Costly Physical Prototypes\\n\\nReduce the amount of expensive physical prototypes that are needed in the process of designing and manufacturing a product. With Shapr3D on Vision Pro, you can create fully editable digital prototypes that allow for quick adjustments without committing to physical builds. [...] Two people talking, one of them is wearing an Apple Vision Pro headset viewing a 3D model\\n\\n## An immersive design solution, like no other.\\n\\n### Unparalleled Visual Quality.\\n\\nHarness the unbeatable visual detail and clarity of Apple Vision Pro.\\n\\n### powered by parasolid®\\n\\nWork between any CAD system and craft precise, manufacturing-ready models.\\n\\n## Integral part of the Shapr3D ecosystem.\\n\\nStart modelingSign up [...] EnterpriseProductResources\\nPricing\\n\\nR&D and design\\n\\nConceptual designDesign reviewDigital validation (XR)\\n\\nProduct engineering\\n\\nPrototypingPeer reviewMechanism designSimulation preprocessing\\n\\nManufacturing engineering\\n\\nTool and equipment designAssembly planning in XRDFM review\\n\\nManufacturing ops\\n\\nMaintenance and repairContinuous improvementJig, fixture and end of tool arm tooling designManufacturing tool retrofittingErgonomics testing\\n\\nSales and marketing\\n\\nProject management and Sales\\n\\nFast concepts\\n\\nMultiple devicesCAD toolsAdaptive User InterfaceSiemens Parasolid Kernel\\n\\nCollaborative design\\n\\nShared team spaceBrowser-based review linksFlexible Cloud Storage\\n\\nIntegrated XR\\n\\nReal-time visualizationAR: Core workflow, not a pluginNative on Apple Vision Pro\\n\\nCAD integrations\",\n        \"score\": 0.6654328,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://www.engineering.com/should-engineers-buy-the-apple-vision-pro/\",\n        \"title\": \"Should engineers buy the Apple Vision Pro?\",\n        \"content\": \"“We were excited to get an early look of the Apple Vision Pro,” Greg Brown, vice president of product management for Onshape at PTC, told Engineering.com. “We knew that because of the way that it was going to come out—the functionality, the ease of use and all of these things—the barriers that were previously there in doing this type of visualization would be addressed in a major way.”\\n\\nBrown views the biggest current engineering uses for the Vision Pro as ideation, collaboration, and evaluation, and says these are the areas where the Onshape app has focused first. The current app allows multiple people to interact with a model in the same virtual space. The following video from PTC shows the app in action: [...] ### Apple Vision Pro beyond design\\n\\nEngineering work extends far beyond 3D models, and companies are testing out VR and AR software for use on the manufacturing floor, construction sites and beyond.\\n\\nView from within the Apple Vision Pro Resolve app showing a comment left within a building. (Image: Resolve.) [...] PTC has hinted at plans to bring 3D design tools to the Vision Pro as well, but right now their software is focused on display, rendering and commenting.\\n\\nHungarian CAD provider Shapr3D also offers its 3D design software on the Vision Pro, but the immersive version of the software aims to be much more versatile than mere viewing. The company is offering demos of their Vision Pro software which advertises the ability to design fully in the headset.\\n\\nOther engineering software available for the Apple Vision Pro includes Nvidia Omniverse, which can stream data and applications on the headset; Vectary, an interactive product visualizer; Graphisoft’s BIMx presentation app; and JigSpace, a 3D presentation app.\\n\\n### Apple Vision Pro beyond design\",\n        \"score\": 0.63939893,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      },\n      {\n        \"url\": \"https://poly.cam/vision-pro\",\n        \"title\": \"Native 3D App & 3D Models for Apple Vision Pro - Polycam\",\n        \"content\": \"### Your own 3D sandbox\\n\\nCapture your own environment or find one in our library, then fill it with 3D objects of your choosing. Mix and match different captures and models to your heart's content. Renovate your home, re-imagine your surroundings, or assemble your very own 3D collage - the only limit is your imagination.\\n\\n### Take the next step in immersive 3D.\\n\\nDownload now on the App Store.\\n\\nDownload on the\\n\\nApp Store\\n\\nImage of Apple Vision Pro headset\\n\\n#### Browse 3D models\\n\\nAnatomyDinosaursArchitectureFoodSneakersVehiclesLegoAutoCAD modelsMaya modelsFBX modelsGLTF modelsUnity modelsBlender modelsUnreal engine models\\n\\nOil & gasReal estateHealth careRetail & E-commerseSolar & Renewable energyForensics & Law Enforcement\\n\\nUse case\\n\\nFacilities managementStructural design\\n\\nResources\",\n        \"score\": 0.62633044,\n        \"raw_content\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]","cwd":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/researcher"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772941718451}}
{"type":"message","id":"5088d195","parentId":"e5440a7e","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:49:20.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"我已经收集到了大量关于 Apple Vision Pro 在工业设计领域的案例。现在让我整理这些信息并写入报告文件："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"function.write:6","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/researcher/apple_vision_pro_industrial_design_report.md","content":"# Apple Vision Pro 在工业设计领域的最新案例调研报告\n\n**调研时间：** 2026年3月8日  \n**调研人员：** 老张 (agent-researcher)\n\n---\n\n## 一、概述\n\nApple Vision Pro 自2024年2月发布以来，凭借其空间计算能力和沉浸式体验，在工业设计领域展现出巨大的应用潜力。本报告汇总了 Vision Pro 在工业设计领域的最新应用案例，涵盖汽车制造、CAD设计、3D建模、培训指导等多个方面。\n\n---\n\n## 二、核心工业设计应用案例\n\n### 1. 汽车制造业\n\n#### 保时捷 (Porsche) - 车辆配置与设计\n- **应用场景：** 保时捷推出了\"911 Spirit 70\" App，允许客户在真实环境中以1:1比例查看虚拟保时捷911，并进行实时定制\n- **应用价值：**\n  - 客户可在展厅中沉浸式体验车辆配置\n  - 无需实体样车即可展示全部配置选项\n  - 提升客户购买决策效率和满意度\n\n#### 保时捷 + MHP - 生产线员工培训\n- **合作方：** 保时捷与管理和IT咨询公司MHP\n- **应用场景：** 在德国祖文豪森工厂进行3D培训演示\n- **技术实现：**\n  - 将焊接转台和制造机器人的CAD数据真实映射到培训场景中\n  - 员工可在头戴设备中看到分步骤的操作指导\n  - 3D模型上叠加维修说明\n- **效果：** 提高员工满意度，减少操作错误，支持评估和认证\n\n### 2. CAD与3D建模\n\n#### PTC Onshape Vision\n- **应用场景：** 产品设计师和工程师查看、交互和协作处理复杂3D模型\n- **核心功能：**\n  - 将CAD模型以真实比例投影到物理空间中\n  - 支持多人同时在虚拟空间中协作\n  - 可从各个角度查看内部零件的分层3D模型\n- **应用价值：** 简化设计审查流程，加速原型评估\n\n#### Shapr3D Spatial CAD\n- **特点：** 原生运行在Apple Vision Pro上的CAD软件\n- **核心能力：**\n  - 直接在Vision Pro上进行实时3D设计和编辑\n  - 减少昂贵物理原型的依赖\n  - 支持快速调整设计而无需制作实体样件\n  - 基于Siemens Parasolid内核，确保制造级精度\n- **应用环节：**\n  - 概念设计\n  - 设计审查\n  - 数字验证(XR)\n  - 工具和夹具设计\n\n### 3. 制造业龙头企业应用\n\n#### 大众汽车 (Volkswagen)\n- **应用平台：** Innoactive平台\n- **应用场景：** 借助可视化数字模型评估汽车零部件\n- **价值：** 简化设计流程，提升协作效率\n\n#### EVAPCO (冷却塔制造商)\n- **应用：** 使用JigSpace App\n- **场景：** 在工业厂房中投影3D冷却塔模型\n- **价值：** 全面革新客户教育模式，提供沉浸式产品展示\n\n#### 迪卡侬 (Decathlon)\n- **应用：** 自定义App\n- **场景：** 顾客无需打开包装盒即可体验真实比例的户外装备\n- **价值：** 提升购物体验，减少退货率\n\n### 4. 航空与重工业\n\n#### 荷兰皇家航空公司 (KLM)\n- **应用：** Engine Shop App\n- **场景：**\n  - 技术人员将操作指南叠加在真实比例的大型设备模型上\n  - 按步骤进行喷气发动机维护操作\n  - 确定扭矩序列，确保安装准确\n- **价值：** 减少失误，提升学习速度，缩短上岗准备时间\n\n#### CAE (航空培训)\n- **应用：** 飞行员培训模拟\n- **场景：** 在详细模拟环境中训练飞行员\n- **价值：** 提高知识保留率，为全尺寸模拟器训练做好准备\n\n### 5. 建筑与工程\n\n#### Resolve App\n- **应用场景：** 建筑工程指导\n- **功能：**\n  - 建筑工程师可规划并访问墙体后系统(HVAC、管道、电气、消防喷淋)的决策信息\n  - 替代静态纸质图纸，在Vision Pro上查看高细节平面图和3D模型\n  - 建筑师、建造商和维护人员可查看、修复和评论\n- **价值：** 增强整个建筑项目的生命周期管理\n\n#### BILT 3D Immersive Instructions\n- **应用场景：** 建筑和水电领域专业技师培训\n- **功能：** 在实物旁边放置精细模型进行对照，使用数码分步操作指南\n- **价值：** 更快、更准确、更安全地完成工作\n\n---\n\n## 三、Vision Pro 工业设计核心技术优势\n\n### 1. 空间计算能力\n- 将数字内容与物理世界无缝融合\n- 支持AR、MR、VR多种应用模式\n- 无限画布，可任意缩放和排列应用\n\n### 2. 精准交互技术\n- **眼动追踪：** 视线即鼠标指针\n- **手势识别：** 两指一掐即点击\n- **语音控制：** 支持自然语言指令\n- **空间音频：** 分析空间特征和材质，精确匹配物理环境\n\n### 3. 显示技术\n- **Micro OLED显示屏：** 单眼4K分辨率，双目8K效果\n- **Pancake光学方案：** 3P设计，折叠光路实现轻薄\n- **自动瞳距调节：** 电机自动调整镜片位置\n\n### 4. 传感器阵列\n- 12个摄像头\n- 5个传感器(1个LiDAR、2个结构光深度传感、2个IR传感)\n- 6个麦克风\n- 实现精准的环境感知和空间定位\n\n---\n\n## 四、工业设计领域应用价值总结\n\n| 应用领域 | 核心价值 | 代表企业 |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| 汽车设计 | 虚拟配置、沉浸式展示、员工培训 | 保时捷、大众 |\n| CAD/3D建模 | 实时协作、减少物理原型、加速设计迭代 | PTC、Shapr3D |\n| 制造业 | 数字孪生、远程指导、客户教育 | EVAPCO、迪卡侬 |\n| 航空/重工业 | 模拟培训、维护指导、操作标准化 | KLM、CAE |\n| 建筑工程 | 3D可视化、施工指导、设施管理 | Resolve |\n\n---\n\n## 五、发展趋势与展望\n\n### 1. 企业级应用加速\n- Apple已宣布Enterprise Spatial Design Lab，为企业提供从概念到落地的支持\n- Deloitte成立Apple Vision Pro学院，培训超过100名visionOS解决方案交付专家\n\n### 2. 2025年M5芯片升级\n- 更强大的M5芯片带来AI能力增强\n- Dual Knit Band改进长时间佩戴舒适度\n- 对专业用户和开发者更加友好\n\n### 3. 工业4.0深度融合\n- 与数字孪生技术深度结合\n- 支持工业物联网(IIoT)数据可视化\n- 推动智能制造和远程协作\n\n---\n\n## 六、参考资料\n\n1. Apple 官方企业应用页面: https://www.apple.com/business/enterprise/apple-vision-pro/\n2. PTC Onshape Vision案例: https://www.onshape.com/en/blog/apple-vision-pro-cad-app-use-cases\n3. Porsche Vision Pro应用: https://www.forbes.com/sites/alexlevin/2025/04/24/porsches-new-apple-vision-pro-app-lets-you-design-your-dream-911/\n4. Porsche & MHP培训案例: https://manufacturingdigital.com/articles/porsche-ag-mhp-virtual-training-uses-apple-vision-pro\n5. Shapr3D Spatial CAD: https://www.shapr3d.com/products/vision-os\n6. Apple Newsroom企业应用发布: https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/04/apple-vision-pro-brings-a-new-era-of-spatial-computing-to-business/\n\n---\n\n**报告完成，准备交接给 agent-writer 进行文章撰写。**\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":22275,"output":1835,"cacheRead":768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24878,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772941718463}}
